title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and form a ball.
Roll ball in the ground pecans.

title: eggnog bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Generously grease Bundt pan and press chopped nuts and candied cherries on bottom and sides of pan. Combine cake mix, butter, nutmeg, eggs, eggnog and rum or rum flavoring. Beat until smooth 4 to 5 minutes. Pour into pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes until cake tests done with a toothpick. Cool 10 minutes and invert. Dust with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and add small amount buttermilk.
Mix.
Add sugar, flour and salt; beat all until smooth.
Add buttermilk and butter.
Cook in skillet on top of stove until thick.
Stir constantly to prevent sticking.
Pour into baked pie crust and top with meringue.
Bake until browned.

title: granola mix bars
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add the last 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Watch closely so they don't burn.
Cool on paper towels. Cut them up.
Eat them as snack or put jelly on top and eat them for breakfast.

title: orange cake
directions: Combine hot water and Jell-O.
Combine all other ingredients and add cooled Jell-O.
Bake in Bundt or angel food cake pan at 325° until done.

title: campfire potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes in aluminum foil.
Add onions, butter and cheese; season to taste.
Wrap up in aluminum foil.
Put on fire for about 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: autumn apple cake
directions: In a small bowl, soak currants or raisins in water for 1 hour. Drain. Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In a large bowl, with electric mixer, beat oil and sugars until well blended, about 6 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla, then gradually beat in flour mixture. Fold currants into batter along with apples and pecans. Preheat oven to 350°.
Spoon batter into 9-inch greased tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours. Remove from oven and cool on wire rack.

title: ship ashore cheese fondue
directions: Mix ingredients together and heat in double boiler until cheese is melted.
Do not overheat nor dilute with water.
Serve with bread sticks or crackers.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Peel
and
put in bowl.
Add butter, sugar and eggs and mix well.
Add nutmeg, milk, orange juice and extract;	blend
well.
Pour
into
shell.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Mix pineapple with cheese in casserole dish.
Mix juice, flour and sugar; heat enough to blend well.
Pour the mixture over pineapple and cheese.
Crumble crackers over mixture.
Pour melted butter over the mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: big mama carlisle's banana pudding
directions: Fix wafers and bananas.
Add sugar with flour.
Then add eggs, that have been slightly beaten.
Add milk.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and oleo.
Mix and pour over wafers and bananas.

title: deboned chicken breasts
directions: Wash and salt chicken breast halves.
Roll each in a half piece of bacon.
Place slices of dried beef on bottom of greased (Pam) baking dish.
Place 1 rolled breast on top of each slice of dried beef.
Stir soup and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Cover with silver foil.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours, covered, and 1 hour uncovered.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Fry hamburger.
Drain. Mix well the mushroom soup and milk together.
Stir into hamburger.
Heat in microwave 5 to 8 minutes. Serve in buns.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered milk and honey or brown sugar (sweetened to your taste).
Add any one of these that you like to give crunchiness: granola, sunflower seeds, coconut or raisins. Roll into balls or logs (to slice).
Roll in sesame seed or flaked coconut.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients and let set in refrigerator for 30 minutes. Take out, form into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: hot chip dip
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain well.
Mix all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with large tortilla chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Cool and remove from bone.
Add soup, broth and sour cream.
Mix well.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Dot with oleo.
Bake until bubbly at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in casserole.
Crumble potato chips on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add taco sauce, chopped pepper and soup.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour half of mixture in a casserole dish.
Place half of the chips on top of mixture. Spread layer of cheese.
Repeat process with remaining meat sauce, chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix these into a batter.
Grease a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan. Line with wax paper and grease wax paper.
Spread batter into pan. Sprinkle with 1 cup chopped walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; turn over on towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Roll lengthwise and let cool.

title: sandy's apple cake
directions: Dump altogether and mix with wooden spoon until completely mixed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onions and celery in oleo.
Mix in rest of ingredients. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green peppers with crab meat
directions: Cut tops off peppers; remove seeds. Parboil peppers 5 minutes. Drain. Scald cream; add butter and nutmeg. Mix cornstarch, wine, lemon juice and salt. Add to cream. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Combine with crab meat and rice and spoon into peppers. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake in a greased baking dish in a moderate oven (350°) for 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough into 13 x 9-inch or two round pans sprayed with Pam.
Bake as directed.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese together with sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Spread on cooled crust. Garnish with sliced fruits.
Add chopped pineapple before serving.

title: broccoli hot dish
directions: Combine.
Place in casserole and top with grated sharp Cheddar cheese. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken veronique
directions: Combine salt, white
pepper
and
1/2 teaspoon paprika; mix well.
Place chicken in a
lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle salt
mixture evenly over chicken.
Add 1/2 cup wine, lemon
juice,
celery, chives and tarragon;
dot with 1/4 cup butter.
Bake, covered at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste chicken with remaining 1/2 cup wine every 20 minutes.
(Recipe can be made to this point and refrigerated up to 2 days ahead; reheat
before proceeding.) Remove to a warm serving platter; reserve pan drippings.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper. Brown in a nonstick skillet or with a little oil and set aside. Put UNCOOKED RICE in a baking dish. Top with onion, bell pepper and drained mushrooms. Place pork chops on top. Dissolve bouillon in boiling water. Pour over chops. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash and boil to your tenderness.
In a big bowl, mix well squash, 2 eggs, chopped onions, cream of mushroom soup and Cheddar cheese.
After mixing well, pour in a long casserole dish. Top with more cheese (as much as you like) and crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake in the oven for approximately 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apples, spices and sugar; put in cake pan.
Mix flour, sugar, butter and salt; mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Cream butter; add next five ingredients and
cream well. Chill.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Bake in slow 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Place 2 to 3 at a time in bag of sugar; shake ever so gently.
Cool on rack.

title: watermelon sherbet
directions: Use round bottom bowl sprayed with Pam.
Spread lime sherbet on bottom and sides of bowl.
Freeze 1/2 hour until firm.
Spread thin layer of lemon or pineapple sherbet.
Freeze again until firm.
Blend raspberry sherbet with chocolate bits, fill the bowl and freeze for several hours.
Unmold onto serving dish and slice like watermelon.

title: granny p.c.'s green tomato pickles
directions: Soak tomatoes for 24 hours which have been sliced thin in cold water that has lime in it.
At the end of 24 hours, rinse tomatoes, being careful not to break, as they are very crisp.
Soak for 4 hours in fresh water, changing water ever hour.
Drain well.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix and bake according to package directions (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pan.
Let cool and crumble.
Prepare pudding mix according to directions.
Place 1/3 of the crumbled brownies in a trifle bowl.
Top with 1/3 of pudding mix, 1/3 of Cool Whip and 1/3 of crushed candy bars.
Repeat layers twice with remaining ingredients, ending with crushed candy bars on top.
Chill 8 hours or overnight.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sugars, milk and butter. Cook until a soft ball forms in cold water (235°).
Just before removing pan from heat, add remaining ingredients.
Stir until marshmallows are almost melted.
Remove from heat. Beat until mixture begins to thicken, about 1 minute.
Pour immediately into buttered 8-inch square pan. When cool, cut into serving sized pieces.
Yields 1 1/2 pounds.

title: broccoli oriental
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook fresh broccoli and water chestnuts, covered, in a small amount of boiling water for 9 to 11 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain; transfer to bowl.
Keep warm.

title: butterscotch noodles
directions: Melt butterscotch bits over hot water.
Cool slightly.
Stir in noodles and peanuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: blue grapey cooler
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a 1 1/2-gallon pitcher and stir well.
Add sparkling water just before serving.
Serve immediately.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: cheddar beer bread
directions: This takes only 10 minutes to put together and you'll look like a pro!

title: one loaf bread
directions: Pour 1-1/4 c. warm water into a medium size bowl. Add 2 Tbsp. sugar (white) and 2 Tbsp. soft shortening, 1 tsp. salt. Add 1-1/2 c. flour, blend with mixer at medium speed for about 3 minutes. Scrape the bowl and remove beaters and add 1-1/2 c. flour; beat with spoon until well mixed.

Round the dough, cover with cloth, set it free from draft until double in bulk (about 1 hour). Stir down with spoon, pour into greased loaf pan, smooth top round like a loaf. Cover and let rise until within
a 1/2 inch of the top of the pan. Bake in 375° preheated oven 40 minutes. Check before the 40 minutes, it may be done and have a hollow thump when hit with a knuckle.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with salt until almost done.
Pour off water and put potatoes in casserole dish.
Pour margarine over potatoes, then sprinkle with paprika, garlic powder and dry parsley.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pickled carrots
directions: In saucepan cook carrots in boiling salted water to cover, 3 to 5 minutes or until tender-crisp.

title: chocolate ecstasy
directions: In large bowl, place Juliette crumbs on bottom.
Pour Kahlua over top of crumbs.
Mix the mousse according to package directions.
Layer half the mousse, half the whipped topping and half the Heath bits.
Repeat with remaining half of mousse, whipped topping and Heath bits.
Chill overnight.

title: cottage pudding
directions: In saucepan, bring to boil the hot water, 1 cup brown sugar and 1 tablespoon butter.
Boil 3 minutes.
Place in bottom of 8 x 8 baking dish.

title: sausage scramble
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cook and stir sausage over medium heat until light brown; drain.
Place sausage in greased baking dish, 13 x 8 x 2-inch.
In a separate bowl, beat together eggs and milk; stir in cheese.
Pour egg mixture on sausage.
Sprinkle with croutons.
Bake, uncovered, until knife inserted in center comes out clean (45 to 55 minutes).
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: There are no set measurements.
Add ingredients in quantities needed.
Mix together; let sit overnight in refrigerator.
May need to add more dressing.

title: lizzie's linguini
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in frying pan.
Add bacon and sausage; cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Add garlic; cook 1 minute longer.
With slotted spoon, transfer bacon, sausage and garlic to a bowl and reserve.
Add butter to the juices in the frying pan.
Add onion and carrot; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until vegetables are just beginning to soften but are still crisp.
Transfer vegetables to bowl with bacon and sausage. Add zucchini pieces and cook, stirring constantly, until they are barely tender.
Do not let the zucchini turn brown.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat eggs; mix flour with sugar and add to eggs gradually.
Add flavoring, then add milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes in 450° oven.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: In a bowl mix fresh ground beef and rice; season with salt to taste.
Make into round 2-inch meatballs.
Brown in a large skillet.
Add tomato soup.
Simmer until they are done.

title: honey-peanut squares
directions: Butter square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
In large saucepan, stir together sugar and honey.
Cook and stir over medium heat just until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in cereal and peanuts until well coated. Turn into pan; pat mixture evenly with buttered back of spoon or hand.
Cool; cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix gelatin and Jell-O together, then dissolve in boiling water.
Cool.
Add strawberries and pineapple.
Chill half of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan until firm.
Spread sour cream over firm layer.
Cover and chill until firm.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and mango.
Add tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes and garlic.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Cook down until thick.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Melt butter.
Crunch up dry noodles and add to butter.
Add sesame seed and almonds.
Brown in butter lightly.
Set aside for 20 minutes to cool.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Slightly beat egg in mixing bowl add milk.
Stir in cornbread mix.
Add all other ingredients mix well.
Pour into non-stick baking dish.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate fondue
directions: Melt ingredients in pan over low heat while stirring.
Keep warm while dipping bite-size pieces of fruit such as bananas, apples, oranges, cherries, strawberries, pineapple, etc.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cantaloupe pie
directions: Cook until thick, pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: e-z sticky buns
directions: Let bread dough thaw.
Knead for 1 minute.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecan halves or walnuts in bottom of pan evenly.
Roll 1 loaf of bread into little balls and lay evenly in pan.
Blend vanilla pudding, butter and milk and pour over balls. Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll second loaf into little balls and press into mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap and let stand for 2 hours to rise (warm place).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: overnite buns
directions: Sift 8 cups flour in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, salt and yeast.
Stir well.
Use tap water as hot as it comes from the tap. Add water, oil and beaten eggs all at once.
Stir well.
Then add one more cup flour at a time until dough forms a ball.
Do not make dough too stiff.
Turn out on floured board and knead until elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn and let rise.
Punch down and let rise.
Form into desired rolls.
Put on greased pans and let rise.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir well and serve over ice.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Combine everything (except butter).
Mix well.
Reserve 1/2 of cracker crumbs.
Spoon rest of mixture into well-greased baking dish.
Melt butter.
Pour over crackers.
Brown and mix.
Sprinkle over top of chicken mixture.
Cook at 350° until chicken is done and vegetables are tender.

title: muffins (using biscuit mix)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Lightly grease muffin tins. Stir mix and sugar together. Mix water and egg thoroughly; add to mix and sugar. Stir until dry ingredients are barely moistened. Batter will be lumpy. Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake until lightly browned, about 20 minutes.

title: happy day or one-bowl cake
directions: Measure into a sifter the first 4 ingredients.
Measure the shortening into a mixing bowl.
Stir shortening just to soften. Add dry ingredients and about 3/4 cup of milk.
Beat 2 minutes. Add eggs and remaining milk and beat 1 minute longer. Bake in moderate oven.

title: meat loaf a-la-tracye
directions: Mix chopped green pepper and celery in ground beef.
Add basil, oregano and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Mix in tomato sauce and teriyaki sauce.
After thoroughly mixed, make into loaf. Place in square baking pan.
Place in preheated oven at 350° for about an hour or more.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dewberry cream pie
directions: Place berries in pie shell.
Mix next 3 ingredients.
Add next 2 ingredients.
Pour mixture over berries and allow to settle to bottom.
Mix last 3 ingredients.
Mixture should be crumbly. Spread over top of pie.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: taco chip casserole
directions: Cook hamburger until light brown, stirring frequently.
Add onions and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add soup, water and tomatoes; add salt to taste.
Cook until bubbly.
In a large casserole dish, put layer of taco chips, then hamburger mixture. Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Top with cheese and heat in 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook mixture 10 minutes.
Add 1 pound sliced or chopped beef. Cook on low for 1 hour.
Serve on buns.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown onion in fat.
Add meat and cook slowly, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until meat is tender and flavors are blended, about 40 minutes.

title: orange flip
directions: Pour boiling water over tapioca pudding and orange jello. Place in refrigerator until thick.
Mix once in a while.
Drain oranges.
Fold in oranges and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Keep refrigerated.

title: apple raisin slaw
directions: Mix apples with lemon juice in a large bowl.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: super corn bread
directions: Put 2 teaspoons oil in small iron skillet; put in 400° oven until skillet is hot.
Mix all ingredients well; pour in hot skillet and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: pineapple tofu cheese cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Pour in 8-inch pie crust made of graham crackers.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: santa fe baked apple dumplings
directions: Peel, cut in halves and core large tart apples.
Make a dough as follows:
Take 2 1/2 cupfuls of flour, a heaping teaspoonful of baking powder, 1 teaspoonful of salt and sift together.
Rub 2/3 of a cupful of lard with the flour.
Mix with enough cold water to make a dough easily handled.
Divide the dough into 6 parts. Roll each part large enough to enclose half an apple.
Press the dough firmly around each piece of apple and bake in a moderate oven.
Serve with sweetened cream, flavored with lemon or any preferred flavoring.

title: cantaloupe pie
directions: Sift the flour and salt together.
Cut shortening into the flour mixture until the mixture looks like coarse meal. Add milk slowly until all of the flour is moistened.
Roll out pastry thin.

title: mrs. english's pound cake
directions: Cream margarine thoroughly; add sugar in 3 or 4 parts, and beat a little after each addition.
Add flavor and mix well.
Sift flour, measure and then sift 3 times.
To creamed mixture, add flour alternately with one egg at a time, beating after each addition.
(Begin and end with flour.)
Bake in tube pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 300° or 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook syrup, sugar and water to 280° on candy thermometer; add nuts and cook to 300°.
Add margarine and soda; stir in gently, but quickly.
Pour onto large greased cookie sheet.
Spread without using a spoon too much.
Cool; break into pieces.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix in order given and bake in greased pan in 375° oven for 40 minutes.

title: slop cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Good served with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: pineapple bisque
directions: Combine crushed pineapple, granulated sugar and cornstarch; cook until thick and clear.
Cool.

title: strawberry lemonade
directions: *Garnishes could be more strawberries and/or mint leaves.

title: beef and mac casserole
directions: Fix macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Brown meat and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in baking dish and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: peas and mushrooms
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown; add peas and mushrooms.
Stir in sugar, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cover and cook over low heat
until hot through.

title: high-rise apple pancake
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet over low heat.
Add combined apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Cook until apples are tender. Combine eggs, flour, milk and salt; heat until smooth.
Heat oven-proof 8-inch skillet or pan in a 450° oven until very hot. Coat skillet with margarine; immediately pour in butter.
Bake on lowest rack at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; continue baking 10 minutes more or until golden.
Fill with apple mixture; top with preserves.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased casserole at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pumpkin-apple butter pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shell; bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat in oven to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: blueberry squares
directions: Blend butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Grease and flour rectangle size pan.
Spread thick around edges.
Pour blueberry pie filling or blueberries on top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: grilled loin of pork with tart cherry sauce
directions: Lightly sprinkle roast with salt and pepper.
Place on rack in roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer so tip is in center of meat.
Roast at 325° until the thermometer registers 170°, about 2 hours.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar a little at a time; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well. Sift flour, baking powder and salt three times.
Add flour mixture a little at a time and mix thoroughly.
Add flavoring.
Chill dough. Roll dough very thin and cut in desired shape.
Bake in a 400° oven for 6 to 10 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk, butter and salt to a boil.
Stir constantly; boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chips, nuts and vanilla.
Stir chips until chips are melted.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: pea salad extra(serves 6 or more)
directions: Drain grease from bacon.
Combine all ingredients together. Place in refrigerator and serve cold.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook Tater Tots half done.
Mix hamburger, Tater Tots and 1 can of soup.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Pour and spread the other can of soup on top and cook until heated.

title: crystal's favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl mix brown sugar, white sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add shortening; mix well.
Add flour; mix well.
Sprinkle in salt, baking soda and water.
Mix well.
Mix in chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonful onto a cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes until browned.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan.
Beat sugar, oil, pumpkin and eggs in large mixer bowl.
Stir in baking mix, cinnamon and raisins.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.

title: leon's bean dip supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with your favorite snack dipper, like Fritos.

title: sausages and beans
directions: Wash escarole, place in 1 cup boiling water, which 1 teaspoon of salt has been added.
Bring to boil, approximately 2 minutes. Remove escarole, reserve liquid to be added later.
Chop escarole and fold into the following ingredients.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pack into greased 9x13 inch pan.
Use broth to moisten.
Bake at 350°for 45-60 minutes.

title: penne pasta bake
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, drain. Cook meat and onion in a large skillet over medium heat for 5 minutes, drain. Stir in tomato sauce, undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, and 1/2 cup water.Cook, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes. Layer 1/2 pasta, 1/2 sauce, and 1/2 cheese in a 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Repeat. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: very "gude" punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients as you would do for a pitcher of Kool-Aid in a large punch bowl; sweeten to your liking.
Add pineapple juice.
Stir vigorously with each addition.
Add pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Add desired amount of ginger ale. Chill by adding ice or ice ring.
Serves 25 to 30 people.

title: chocolate mint pudding
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Gradually add milk, stirring with a wire whisk until smooth.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, 25 to 30 minutes or until mixture is thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in creme de menthe and vanilla.
Spoon mixture into individual dessert dishes.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Just before serving, sprinkle evenly with crushed peppermint.
Makes about 7 servings.

title: rice-broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Cook enough rice to yield 2 cups.
Thaw broccoli and drain thoroughly.
Saut onion and celery in melted butter.
Blend in soup, milk, chestnuts, rice, broccoli and 1/3 jar of softened cheese spread (set jar in hot water).
Turn into 10 x 7 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake uncovered at 350°
for
30 to 45 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Thaw
potatoes	enough	to
separate.
Melt
margarine. Combine 1/2 cup of margarine with potatoes, onion, sour cream, soup, salt, pepper	and
cups of cheese.
Mix well and pour into
a
quart flat baking dish.
Combine bread crumbs with remaining melted butter and grated cheese.
Sprinkle over top of potato mixture.	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix oleo, pretzels and 3 Tbsp. sugar.
Press into 9 X 13 pan. Bake 8 minutes at 400.
Cool before
continuing.
Mix cream cheese and 1 Cup sugar, cream well.
Fold in cool whip.
Spread over pretzel crust.
Mix strawberries jello and boiling water, add to this strawberries.
Let stand 10 minutes before pouring over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate over night or 8 hours before serving.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spinach as package directs.
Drain well.
Combine spinach with other ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole. Bake 30 minutes.
Top with extra cheese.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar, butter and eggs.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 300 degrees for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: applesauce cocoa cookies(diabetic)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar replacement.
Add egg; blend well. Add dry ingredients with applesauce and water to creamed mixture. Be sure to add flour first and last.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese roll
directions: Blend together all ingredients, except chili powder.
Roll into two logs.
Sprinkle chili powder on wax paper.
Roll logs until lightly covered.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate two days.

title: ice cream
directions: Boil the first 5 ingredients together.
Beat the eggs with 1/2 cup sugar and the cream.
Whip this and fill freezer with milk.

title: yellow cake with caramel icing
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco. Add eggs, flour, baking powder and salt to mixture, alternating with milk and flavorings. Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Remove from pan while warm.

title: dipped peanut butter sandwich cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter on half of the crackers; top with remaining crackers to make sandwiches.
Refrigerate.
In a double boiler over simmering water, melt chocolate chips and shortening, stirring until smooth.
Dip sandwiches and place on waxed paper until chocolate hardens.
Great gift idea for children to give!

title: angel food delight
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add next 5 ingredients in order.
Chill until syrupy.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed on package.
Break up cake into pieces.
Toss lightly with gelatin mix.
Top with Dream Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: tuna and shrimp casserole
directions: Mix shrimp, tuna, celery, lemon juice, bell pepper, onion, hot sauce, salt, pepper and mayonnaise together.
Mix soup, rice and milk together before combining with mayonnaise mixture.
Put into a greased baking dish and cover top with potato chips.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on pan with sides (cookie sheet or pizza pan) and spread cooked sausage over rolls.
Add potatoes and cheese and pour beaten eggs over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: good chicken casserole
directions: Combine dressing mix and butter.
Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with a little over one-half of dressing mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over dressing.
Add remaining dressing mixture.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil; bake until brown.
Serves 12.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients, using half of the Chinese noodles.
Top with remaining noodles and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken or turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8.
You can add mandarin oranges to stretch.

title: skillet hamburger pie
directions: In skillet (350°), brown meat, onions and celery.
Add tablespoon Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper, 16 ounce can cut green beans (drained) and 1/2 cup water.
Make gravy and add. Turn heat to 220°.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Make mashed potatoes; make piles of potatoes on top of mix.
Lay piece of cheese on each pile; cover until cheese is melted, then serve.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Heat broiler.
Scrub potatoes.
Slice potatoes in half lengthwise; slice each half crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
In plastic bag, shake potato slices with dressing until well coated. Arrange slices in single layer on broiler pan.
Broil 4 to 6 inches from heat for 12 to 15 minutes or until tender, turning once.
Serves 4.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs. Pat out in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and 1 stick of margarine (melted).
Spread on graham cracker crust.
Slice bananas and arrange on top; put bananas close together.
Spread drained pineapple over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with cherries and chopped nuts.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine butter flavor Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until blended. Beat egg into creamed mixture. Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix in creamed mixture just until blended. Stir in chocolate chips and pecan pieces.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 3-inches apart onto an ungreased baking sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes. Do not overbake.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, pour in pineapple and pie filling. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Slice butter in thin pieces and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes.

title: chili with broiled bananas
directions: Break up beef in Dutch oven or kettle.
Add onion, garlic, green pepper and celery.
Cook, stirring frequently until beef is brown and vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder, sugar, salt, bay leaf, oregano and basil.
Cook over moderate heat for 30 minutes.
Add kidney beans; cook 15 minutes longer.
Just before serving, peel bananas.
Cut in half lengthwise, brush with melted butter or margarine and broil about 2 minutes.
Just until tender.
Place 2 banana halves on each plate and top with chili.
Makes 8 servings.

title: quick chicken enchiladas
directions: Drain and flake chicken.
Mix with onions and half of cheese. Spread in center of tortillas and roll up.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and drained chilies.
Pour over enchiladas and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through and the cheese is melted.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix the ingredients well.
Spread in a dish.
Top with chopped lettuce, onions, peppers, tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: ripe cucumber pickles
directions: Peel and remove seeds from ripe cucumbers.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until tender.
Process as desired.

title: deep dish chocolate cake
directions: In a
large
bowl,
combine
dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, milk and
vanilla.	Mix 2 minutes on high speed.
Mix in 1 cup boiling water (batter will be thin).
Mix 1 cup water by hand into batter.
Pour
into
13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes or
until	toothpick
comes out clean.
Cool on rack.

title: ham or chicken casserole
directions: Grate cheese and combine all ingredients; put into a casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Peas, parsley and green pepper may also be added, if desired.

title: almond tea punch
directions: Make a simple syrup of sugar and water.
Mix all ingredients together. Chill.
Add chilled ginger ale just before serving. Makes 1 gallon.

title: garnet sparkle
directions: Combine, stir and enjoy!

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.

title: butter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup water.
Mix butter and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Let stand in greased, covered bowl in refrigerator all night or for 6 hours. Roll out as you would biscuits.
Let rise at room temperature until doubled in size.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: hamburger bake
directions: Brown hamburger with bell pepper and onion.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 5 minutes.
Cook macaroni and drain.
When macaroni is drained, add Cheddar cheese and kidney beans.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: nana's pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until wet and pour into ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with whipped topping when cake is cooled.

title: dump cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Dump pineapple into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Dup can of cherry pie filling in dish.
Then dump 1 box yellow or white cake mix over top.
Pour 1 stick of margarine over that and bake 1 hour.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients and spread into pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, 25 to 35 minutes.
Cut in 2 x 1-inch pieces.
Serve warm or cold.

title: hot cheddar olive bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, mix cheese, mayonnaise, onions and chili powder; stir well.
Spread on each half of bread. Arrange olives on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peach pie alaska
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cream by spoonful. Stir until melted and smooth.
Blend in Cool Whip and fruit. Chill if necessary until mixture mounds.
Spoon into crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Garnish.

title: apple butter
directions: Wash apples.
Slice with skin and seeds.
Add cider and cook until apples are very soft.
Put apples through sieve; add sugar and spices; let simmer until quite thick.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking.
Fill in sterilized jars and seal.

title: quick tomato spice cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
If desired, fold in chopped nuts.
Bake as directed on cake mix package.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, salt, flour and baking powder. Beat until creamy.
Add hot milk (not boiling) and vanilla.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° until done.

title: french cream apple pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients and sprinkle 1/2 on bottom of pie shell. Put apples on top of the dry ingredients.
Cover with other 1/2 of dry ingredients.
Pour 1/2 cup cream over all.
Dot with the butter and bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then 350° for about 45 minutes, until apples are tender.

title: spanish eggs
directions: Cook onion with margarine over medium heat.
Cook tomato and pepper with onion for 5 minutes in medium bowl.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour into skillet with onion, etc.
Cook, stirring until eggs are done.

title: pink panther salad
directions: Drain pineapple; set aside.
Cream cottage cheese and Jell-O together until mixture is creamy and thick.
Add pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: pecan thins
directions: Place all ingredients except eggs in bowl.
Mix for 3 to 5 minutes by hand.
When ingredients begin to make a mass, add egg and mix to smooth dough.
Divide into 2 pieces and shape into 2 rolls that are 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Roll in wax paper and chill overnight.
Slice 1/8-inch thin and place on lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Cookies become crispy when cooling.

title: millionaires
directions: Put water and caramel candy pieces in bowl.
Microwave on High; stir until melted.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Dip onto buttered cookie sheet.
Place in refrigerator 2 hours.
Melt chocolate bark in microwave.
Dip chilled candy into melted chocolate.
Lay on wax paper.

title: favorite pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour alternately with whipping cream.
Add vanilla.
Put in well-greased tube pan and bake.
This is a large cake.

title: russian tea cookies
directions: Beat butter until fluffy.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour and salt and stir into butter mixture.
Add nuts.
Chill dough for 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add rest of ingredients in order given.
Put in jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
If a cake pan is used, bake until tests done.

title: bubble coffee cake bread
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle pecans on bottom of pan.
Place frozen rolls around pan.
Sprinkle pudding (not mixed) over rolls. Melt oleo; mix in brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over rolls. Cover with waxed paper and towel.
Leave overnight.
The next morning, bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn out on plate.

title: brown rice #2
directions: Melt the margarine in skillet and put in chopped onion; season with a little salt.
Then add all other ingredients.
Stir and put in a tightly covered Pyrex dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: steak diane(for 2)
directions: Sprinkle steak with salt and pepper.
Combine 1 tablespoon butter and dry mustard in skillet.
Heat until sizzling.
Add steaks.
Cook for 1 minute on each side.
Place on heated serving plate.
Add 1 tablespoon butter, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce to skillet.
Cook over high heat until thickened.
Stir in chives and parsley.
Spoon over steak.
Yields 2 servings.

title: lime pear congealed salad
directions: Heat juice from pears and dissolve jello in the juice.
Add this to the cream cheese and blend until smooth.
Let it begin to gel and then add lemon juice, chopped pears and Cool Whip. Congeal.

title: "junk soup"
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage and onion.
Add Ranch and taco mix. Then add all of the other "junk."
Simmer as you would for chili or a stew for the flavor to set in.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Cook pie shells at 350° for about 10 minutes. Line with browned, drained sausage. Cover with cheese. Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over sausage and cheese. Sprinkle with paprika and dot with butter.
Bake for 35 to 40 more minutes.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream the shortening, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar together.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Blend in the dry ingredients.
Shape by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Roll in sugar; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven and place a solid milk chocolate candy kiss on top of each cookie, pressing down so that cookies crack around the edge.
Return to oven; bake 2 to 4 minutes longer.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy brownies
directions: Mix and bake at 400°.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Brown and drain ground beef.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, mix ground beef, corn, creamed corn, peas and green beans together.
Spread mashed potatoes over the top.
Salt and pepper.
Place pan on a cookie sheet and put in the oven until top is golden brown.
Bake at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine cheese and milk.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted and smooth.
Add corn, eggs, green pepper, basil and pepper. Mix well.
Spoon into baking dish, 6 x 10-inch.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin jazz
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, milk, spices, vanilla and pumpkin.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with dry cake mix.
Dribble the melted butter over the cake mix and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: crunchy spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill overnight to blend flavors.
Hollow out sourdough round, baste with olive oil and sprinkle with garlic powder.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Fill with vegetable mixture.
Serve with baked bread cubes and fresh vegetables.

title: barbecued buns
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add meat and onion.
Cook until lightly browned.
Mix green pepper, seasonings, mustard, vinegar, brown sugar and catsup.
Bring to a boil.
Cover tightly.
Switch to a simmer position for several hours.
Add a little water if mixture gets too thick.
Stir occasionally.
Serve on warm, buttered buns.
Makes 18.

title: beef and cheese loaf
directions: Combine the ground beef, bell pepper and onion.
Add tomato sauce and simmer for 10 minutes.
Beat egg and add to cheese; mix well.
On a cookie sheet, spread one package crescent rolls on the bottom.
Top with the egg and cheese mixture.
Add beef mixture. Put the other can of crescent rolls on top.
Seal edges.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: Place cubed bread, cheese and sausage in layers in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix together eggs, milk and custard. Pour over ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients (except cornbread mix).
After all is well blended, add cornbread mix.
Beat well. Pour into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Bake 25 minutes. Absolutely wonderful!

title: spicy pumpkin loaf
directions: Heat oven
to
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Put all
ingredients
in
a
mixing bowl and mix.
When mixed well, pour
batter in prepared pan.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes or until toothpick
inserted
in center comes out clean.
Remove pan
from oven and cool 10 minutes.
Remove loaf from pan and cool completely.
Tightly
wrap in aluminum foil.
Loaf keeps well in refrigerator or can be frozen.

title: venison jerky
directions: Slice meat into 1/8-inch thick strips.
Combine meat and all ingredients in a plastic bag; shake well.
Marinate 2 to 3 hours in the refrigerator.

title: chilled creamy cucumber soup
directions: Peel, seed and cut cucumbers into chunks.
Process in a blender or food processor for a short time with 1/2 cup broth.
In large bowl, combine with all other ingredients, except tomatoes, parsley and almonds.
Mix well and chill.
Before serving, stir in tomatoes and parsley.
Garnish with almonds.

title: strawberry angel food dessert(no fat, low sugar)
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Stir in thawed strawberries, sugar and salt; cool.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Fold in cake pieces and pour in 9-inch dish.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours and cut in squares.

title: joyce's smoked sausage and potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Cool, dry, then peel.
Slice thinly.
Combine the onions, garlic, green pepper, flour, salt, chives, parsley and pepper in a small bowl. Stir until well blended.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Prepare broccoli according to package and drain.
Place broccoli in blender with 1 1/2 cups broth; blend until smooth. Mix pureed broccoli with 2 cups broth in medium saucepan.
Simmer over medium heat.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake.
Layer all ingredients in punch bowl.
Reserve some Cool Whip for topping.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Flavor is better if it sets for a while.
This is big enough for a large dinner party.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix soup and eggs with meat; form into balls and place in baking pan.
In saucepan over medium heat blend together cranberry sauce, sugar and kraut until smooth.
Pour over meat balls.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in microwave on High, about 2 minutes; stir.
Bring to boiling; cook 3 minutes.
Take out and add soda. Pour over popcorn in double grocery bag and shake.
Close loosely. Cook on High 1 minute.
Shake bag; cook 1 minute.
Shake; cook 60 seconds.
Shake; cook 30 seconds.
Done.
You may add nuts and other goodies if you like.
Cooking time may vary depending on microwave.
Yields 10 servings.

title: stewed tomatoes with corn
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter, quarter and add tomatoes. Add corn, salt, pepper and sugar.
Simmer 20 minutes, stir occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cut broccoli into 1/4-inch pieces.
Cook in lemon juice and water; drain.
Put into shallow buttered pan.
Mix soup with mayonnaise and curry.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix and put in shell.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: happiness pudding
directions: If prepared carefully and served daily, this will be your favorite recipe.
Serves 2.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in pan.
Bring to a boiling point and start timing the mixture for about 1 1/2 minutes or more.
Take off heat and add oats and vanilla.
Add peanut butter and nuts, if desired.
Beat mixture with a spoon until slightly cooled.
Spoon onto wax paper.
Another favorite!

title: best fried chicken(double crust)
directions: Beat 2 eggs with fork.
Add milk; beat again.
Set aside. Season chicken or seafood with creole seasoning or salt and pepper.
Then put meat in flour; shake off excess, then dip meat in egg mixture.
Take out meat; squeeze out excess batter.
Put meat back in flour; coat well and shake off excess.
After heating oil, lower fire to medium heat.
Place meat in pot on medium heat. Cook until golden brown on both sides.

title: one skillet dinner
directions: Cook crumbled beef in butter in skillet over high heat until browned.
Stir in uncooked noodles, tomato sauce, salt, basil and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and heat 2 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 2 large servings.

title: easy butterscotch chip chocolate cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, oil and eggs in a large bowl; mix well. Stir in butterscotch chips and pecans.
Drop by rounded tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Place on wire rack to cool.

title: wilcox's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Chop mushroom stems.
Mix with other ingredients.
Stuff into mushrooms caps; microwave 4 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time with a small amount of flour. Beat well after each addition. Add flavoring; beat. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Drain clams and save liquor.
Chop.
Fry bacon until lightly brown.
Add onion, green pepper and celery; cook until tender. Add liquor, potatoes, seasonings and clams.
Cook about 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add tomato juice.
Heat.
Serves 6.

title: fettuccine sort of alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package.
Meanwhile, using food processor or blender, process cottage cheese until very smooth. Add Parmesan cheese, milk, egg substitute, garlic, nutmeg, pepper and salt.
Process until smooth.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all, except poppy seed, for 140 minutes at medium speed. Add poppy seed; mix in by hand.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: german skillet
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Rinse sauerkraut and drain.
Put all together and mix well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
The last 15 minutes, put slices of cheese on top and return to oven (uncovered).

title: grandmother's fudge
directions: Stir together, or sift into a mixing bowl, all the dry ingredients.
Add peanut butter, butter and vanilla.
Mix well. Press into an 8-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: squaw bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in balls.
Flatten and fry. Excellent spread with oleo and served with chili.

title: super-crisp country fried chicken
directions: Blend milk and egg.
Combine flour and seasoning in plastic or paper bag.
Shake chicken in the seasoned flour.
Dip chicken pieces in milk-egg mixture.
Shake chicken a second time in seasoning mixture to coat thoroughly and evenly.
Shallow or deep fry in hot oil.
Makes four servings.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Combine crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt, and baking soda.
Mix into creamed mixture until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop rounded tablespoons of dough 3 in. apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 1 sheet of cookies at a time for 8-10 minutes for chewy or 11-13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Do not overbake.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine apples, celery, nuts and raisins.
Blend mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped cream; fold in apple mixture.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in water until done. Remove chicken and debone; set aside. Put cream of chicken soup in broth and bring to a boil. Cut up tortillas and add to broth. Add cut up chicken. Boil with lid on for 15 minutes.

title: california skillet
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Add chopped onion and green bell pepper.
Stir in rice with 2 1/2 cups of water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add grated cheese on top and serve when melted.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cheese cake
directions: Leave cream cheese out at room temperature for 2 hours. Gradually add sugar to cream cheese until well-blended (no lumps). Add eggs, evaporated milk and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Add flour gradually until completely absorbed.
Stir in sour cream. Blend well.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a large glass bowl, layer all ingredients in order given. Do not mix.
Cover dish and refrigerate overnight.
Toss lightly just before serving, if you wish.

title: jelly muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Combine egg, milk and oil; add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Lightly grease muffin cups, fill 2/3 full.
Top each with jelly, jam or preserves.
Bake in a 400° oven about 20 minutes.
Remove from pans and serve warm. Makes 10 to 12.

title: cheese potato delight(microwave cooking)
directions: Defrost frozen potatoes in a 2-quart covered glass casserole for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Microwave, covered, for 10 minutes on High, or until cheese is melted.

title: fudge
directions: Combine milk and 2 squares of chocolate, heating on a low flame until chocolate melts.
Add 1 cup sugar and salt.
Let it dissolve and then add slowly two remaining cups of sugar one at a time.
Turn heat up and bring to a boil.
Add Karo syrup. Continue to stir bubbling fudge until a drop from a spoon forms a soft ball in cold water.
Turn off flame and add vanilla and butter.
Beat until very thick.
When the fudge has a grayish sheen from so much beating, turn out into buttered platters.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 450° until done (or you can bake in the microwave).
Spoon out baked potato and mix with the remaining ingredients.
Fill potato skins with mixture and bake with cheese topping at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: bourbon baked beans
directions: Combine beans, mustard, chili sauce, bourbon and coffee in large pot.
Place slices of pineapple over beans; sprinkle dark brown sugar over fruit.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: kids' pasta salad
directions: About 45 minutes before serving or early in the day, prepare pasta as label directs and drain.

title: parmesan oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, garlic salt and pepper; set aside.
Dip chicken in salad dressing, then dip in bread crumb mixture.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses and mix until well blended.
Add pimiento, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and seasonings.
Mix well.
Chill.
Shape into ball (makes 1 large or 2 small); roll in nuts.

title: cheesy drop biscuits
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Mix shortening in with a fork until crumbly.
Stir in cheese and milk. Drop from a tablespoon onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake for about 15 minutes at 450°.
Yields 12 large biscuits.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together; roll into small balls (should make about 80).
Brown in hot oil.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Sprinkle cucumbers with salt; let stand overnight.
Drain. Add remaining vegetables, sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and water. Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cook slowly until cucumbers look transparent.
Ladle into jars.
Process in hot water bath 5 minutes.

title: amish cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, oil and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add vanilla or juices and nuts.
Sift dry ingredients (flour, salt and soda); add to creamed mixture and mix until blended.
Drop by balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° anywhere from 6 to 12 minutes, depending on size.
They should be a light golden.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Mix and bake brownies as directed on the box.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Dream Whip, milk, vanilla and chocolate pudding together.
Spread over brownies.
Spread Cool Whip on top of this layer.
Mix Heath bar with pecans, if desired and sprinkle on top of Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: filled cabbage leaves
directions: Cook rice in 1 1/2-quarts of water for 15 minutes; drain. Combine with meat and mix well.
Cook cabbage 5 or 10 minutes in large kettle.
In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, put oil, flour and the chopped onion; brown a little.
Fill cabbage leaves.
Add tomato sauce.
Cook under low heat for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: saucy steak
directions: Coat beef steak pieces with flour, pound into beef.
Brown beef in oil in 10-inch skillet, push beef to side.
Cook and stir onion in oil until tender; drain.
Add enough water to potato liquid to measure 1 cup.
Mix potato liquid, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, pepper flakes, instant bouillon, salt and pepper; pour on beef and onion.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer until beef is tender, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours. Rinse beans under running cold water.
Add potatoes and beans to skillet.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beans are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion and celery; drain.
Add sour cream, tomato sauce and milk; simmer until well mixed.
Add rotini noodles; mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Recipe can be doubled. Freezes well.

title: english muffins
directions: Mix until flour is wet.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Stir down and add 1 teaspoon baking soda and 2 teaspoons salt.
Spread 1 cup flour on counter; add dough.
Sprinkle over with 1 cup flour and knead.
Roll out to 3/8-inch thick.
Cut with round cutter to desired size.
Dip in cornmeal, top and bottom.
Let rise 1/2 hour.
Preheat griddle to medium-low (300° to 325°), grease and cook 5 minutes on each side.
Makes 1 to 2 dozen.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice; add soup, milk and pimento.
Layer rice, cheese and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In a buttered 2-quart casserole, put chopped cabbage.
Brown meat and onion; salt and pepper to taste.
Add rice, tomato soup and water to hamburg mixture and simmer 10 minutes.
Pour over cabbage; don't stir.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 2 hours.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash and dry potatoes. Prick potatoes with fork in a few places.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Cut thin slice from tops of potatoes and scoop out all pulp into bowl.
Mash pulp with half and half.
Beat in butter and onions.
Add seasonings. Fry bacon until crisp and crumbly.
Add to potato mixture.
Spoon mixture into potato skins.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° about 15 minutes until cheese melts and bubbles.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve orange Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water.
Drain pineapple juice in 1 cup measurement.
Add enough water to make 1 cup.
Add to Jell-O.
Let set.
Combine cream cheese and sour cream together.
You may add nuts.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Saute onions in butter.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Bring to boil, add noodles and cook, uncovered, for 3 minutes.
Stir in broccoli, including liquid, garlic powder and pepper.
Cook 3 more minutes; add milk and cheese; stir until cheese melts.
This can be doubled and freezes well.

title: quick strawberry cake
directions: Slice cake into 2 or 3 layers.
Put layer down on dish.
Add layer of strawberries.
Add layer of whipped cream.
Repeat.

title: borscht cocktail
directions: Mix all ingredients except yogurt together.
Chill 2 to 3 hours in a covered jar.
Serve in cocktail glasses, topping with 1 tablespoon of yogurt.
Makes 4 servings (yields 2 cups).
Good for diabetic diets.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt; cut shortening into flour with pastry blender or 2 table knives.
Add only enough water to hold dough together.
Chill.
Roll.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pastry shells or one 2-crust pie.

title: ham and egg casserole
directions: Arrange alternate layers of ground ham and sliced eggs in a casserole; add mushrooms between layers.
Pour soup thinned with a little milk over layers.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Heat about 30 minutes at 350°.
Do not add salt.
Some onions may be added to soup or sauce.
Very tasty and a great way to use up scrap ham if you are lucky to have any left.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Wash lettuce, onions and radishes; drain.
Cut into bite size.
Combine cream and French dressing.
Stir to mix smoothly. Cut bacon in small strips and fry crisp.
Pour cream dressing over lettuce and mix.
Pour hot bacon and hot grease over lettuce.
Mix well with forks.
Serve at once.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender or food processor for 30 seconds and serve.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: "german chocolate fudge squares"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix with 1/3 cup evaporated milk and margarine.
Add nuts.
Bake 1/2 of this mixture in 7 x 11-inch pan for 10 minutes at 350°.
Melt all caramels with 1/3 cup milk (evaporated).
Spread caramel mixture on baked cake.
Add chocolate chip morsels to top of caramel mixture.
Spread remaining batter on top of caramel and morsels and bake until done, 20 to 25 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: low-fat cheese sauce
directions: Drain yogurt overnight in a colander lined with paper towel in fridge.
Blend with all other ingredients in food processor until smooth.
Heat and pour over pasta or vegetables.

title: five-minute cheesecake pie
directions: To Toast Almonds:
Spread slivered almonds on a cookie sheet and place in a 350 degree oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate salad dressing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl and beat well.
Grease and flour two 8-inch layer cake pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven of 350° for about 35 minutes. (Cake is done when toothpick comes out dry when inserted in middle of cake.)

title: pear honey
directions: Peel, core and finely chop pears in blender.
Put pears, sugar and lemon juice in kettle over medium heat.
Cook until thickens; stir.
Add pineapple.
Cook 15 minutes.
Pour into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust cups.
Process 20 minutes in boiling water.
Yields 13 (12 ounce) jelly jars.

title: italian roast beef sandwich
directions: Brown roast in oil.
Add the next 6 ingredients.
Cover and cook for 1 hour.
Add sliced onion and mushrooms.
Cover again and cook 1 hour or until meat is very tender.
Add water as needed.

title: coconut cream delight
directions: Mix together and set in refrigerator, except pudding and milk. Cook pudding and milk and let cool completely.
Spread pudding over crust, then spread cream cheese mixture over pudding.
Top with coconut.
Instant pudding can be used.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Drop by tablespoons on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle top of each cookie with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: foolproof meringue
directions: Mix first three ingredients and cook until clear.
Set aside. Add salt to egg whites and whip until foamy or standing in peaks. Add to the first mixture. Continue beating until creamy.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar gradually, beating again until very creamy. Pile on pie.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: almond chocolate cake(with mayonnaise - world war ii)
directions: Combine dates, soda and chocolate in mixing bowl.
Pour boiling water over date mixture; let cool to lukewarm.
Stir in brown sugar and mayonnaise, then add flour and almonds.

title: garlic shrimp broccoli linguine
directions: In large skillet, heat oil over medium high heat.
Add shrimp and broccoli.
Cook until tender, about 5 minutes.	Stir frequently.
Sprinkle with cheese and Mrs. Dash.
Add pasta and toss to combine.

title: toll house cookie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In mixer, blend margarine, eggs, flour and sugars.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream. This pie freezes well.

title: beef stir-fry(low-fat)
directions: Cook meat in nonstick pan until done.
Add all other ingredients; cook until vegetables are done but still crispy. Serve with plain rice or noodles.

title: cheddar spinach quiche
directions: Cook spinach and drain well on paper towel.
Toss Cheddar cheese with flour.
Add spinach, milk, eggs, bacon and seasonings. Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Garnish with additional bacon, if desired.
(I usually double the bacon.)

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix milk with enough lemon juice to make it thick.
Add the pineapple and cherries.
Fold in the Cool Whip and freeze.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Grease crock-pot with shortening.
Mix and put in pot.
Cook on low for 3 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple icebox pie
directions: Beat milk, cream cheese and lemon juice with a mixer until smooth. Add pineapple and stir. Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill at least 3 hours. Sprinkle crushed graham crackers in a circle along top edge of pie to garnish before serving.

title: oh for gosh sakes salad
directions: Boil potatoes only until done.
Cool and peel while warm. Slice thinly.
Sprinkle garlic and onion over potatoes.
Add pepper and the oil.
In cup, add salt, vinegar and boiling water. Stir to dissolve salt.
Pour over potato mixture and mix gently. Salad is to be served warm.
A garnish of sliced hard-boiled eggs, parsley and pickles may be added.
Will serve 6 to 8.

title: yogurt muffins
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine until crumbly. Mix yogurt, eggs and vanilla. Add to dry ingredients.
Mix only until moistened.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello from box with cottage cheese and Dream Whip.
Drain oranges and pineapple and mix with other ingredients.
Add nuts. Keep in refrigerator.

title: ham delights
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Split party rolls in half, horizontally.
Spread mixture on top and bottom of rolls. Cover with shredded ham and cheese square(s).
Put top and bottom halves back together like a sandwich.
Wrap in foil (individually or in a pan covered with foil).
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°. Yields 40 sandwiches.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: polish pound cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and water.
Beat until well blended. Add pudding, cherries and nuts. Stir well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour (no less).

title: granola 'n oats
directions: Measure rolled oats into an 8 x 12-inch microwavable dish. Microwave on High for 2 1/2 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking time.
Stir next 6 ingredients into rolled oats.
Place margarine in 1-cup glass measure.
Microwave on High until melted (40 to 60 seconds).

Combine margarine, honey and vanilla; pour over oatmeal mixture, stirring until completely combined. Microwave on Medium on 50% power until well heated, 7 to 8 minutes, stirring twice during cooking time.
Stir in fruit bits, if desired.
Press mixture firmly again bottom of dish with back of spoon.
Allow to cool; break apart with fork.
Store, tightly covered, for up to 1 week.
(Recipe tested on 500 to 700 watt microwave oven).
Makes 5 cups.

title: dill dip
directions: Serve with cut up vegetables.
Keep refrigerated until use.

title: bubblin' party punch(orange)
directions: In bowl, dissolve jello and sugar in water; set aside.
In large bowl, combine pineapple juice, lemon juice and jello mixture.
Chill.
Just before serving, pour juice mixture into punch bowl.
Add sherbet and club soda.

title: butternut cake
directions: Cream the Crisco, sugar and eggs on high speed for 10 minutes. Add 1 cup flour and beat 1 minute on low speed.
Add rest of flour and milk; beat 1 minute on high speed.
Add flavoring and mix.
Divide batter between 4 layer pans.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until done. Frost between layers, on sides and on top.

title: betty's hot cakes
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk, salt and sugar.
Beat thoroughly.
Add enough flour to make a batter consistency.
Do not beat well, batter should be slightly lumpy.
Add soda and powder.
Stir in oil.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry pie crust as directed on package.
In medium skillet, cook and stir meat until brown; drain. Stir in Sloppy Joes/taco package, bread crumbs, tomato sauce, onion and water.
Turn mixture into pie crust.
Spread Cheese Topping over filling.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Cut into wedges.
Make 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked beans deluxe
directions: Brown ground beef with green pepper and onions.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Mix all together. Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: spaghetti de siciliano
directions: Saute medium onion in olive oil over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Add green pepper, eggplant, garlic and mushrooms and saute for 15 more minutes.	Add tomatoes and basil.
Cover and simmer
for
minutes.
Add
anchovies,	olives, capers and parsley
and
cook 10 minutes more.
Serve over hot spaghetti. Time
of
preparation: Pre-prep: 20 minutes.
Cooking time: 60 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate chip-oatmeal cookies
directions: Remove the margarine or butter from the refrigerator at least 30 minutes before making the cookies.
Turn oven to 375°.
Put margarine or butter in a large bowl.
Beat butter with an electric mixer for 30 seconds.
Add egg, flour, granulated sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and baking soda to the margarine.
Beat on medium speed about 2 minutes or until well mixed.
Stop occasionally to scrape sides of bowl.
Use a wooden spoon to stir in oats and chocolate pieces.
Scoop enough dough on a small spoon so the dough is slightly rounded.
Leave about 2 inches between cookies. Put the cookie sheet in the oven.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Makes 40 cookies.

title: banana split pie
directions: Bake pie shells with nuts sprinkled on the bottom at 375° for 14 to 16 minutes.
Combine pineapple, sugar and flour over low heat for the amount of time it takes to thicken.
The time will vary with different pots and stoves, but it is approximately 3 to 5 minutes.
After shells are baked, let them cool 15 minutes, then layer with half the bananas.
Cover bananas with pineapple, then finally the remaining half of bananas.
Cover with plastic and cool in the refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Quarter cherries; mix cherries and their juice with the Cool Whip and spread across the top of the pies.
Cover and place in the refrigerator.
Make 2 pies at 8 servings each.
Serve cold.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Heat until cheese melts. Combine sauces and broccoli and place in a greased casserole dish. Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef, ground pork, onion and garlic.
Drain fat. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, 2 tablespoons parsley flakes, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and basil.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 1 hour or until consistency of spaghetti sauce.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cottage cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, salt and oregano.
Reserve 1/2 cup meat sauce for thin top layer.
In ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer 1/4 each of noodles, meat sauce, Mozzarella and cottage cheese mixture. Repeat 3 times.
Spread reserved meat sauce over top and sprinkle 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add flavors and baking powder last, beat well. Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour and 35 minutes at 300°.
Do not preheat oven.

title: poppy seed cookies
directions: Cream butter or oleo.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat in egg yolks and vanilla.
Blend in flour, salt and poppy seed.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Place 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheets. Press two chocolate chips in each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: cucumbers in sour cream salad
directions: Slice cucumbers thin, sprinkle with salt and let stand for a couple of hours.
Rinse in cold water and squeeze out.
Mix other ingredients and fold cucumbers into sauce.

title: oven chicken salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together except potato chips.
Spread into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips over top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: coke salad
directions: Add boiling juice from cherries and pineapple to Jell-O.
Cool and add Coke.
Chill until thick, then add remaining ingredients. Chill until firm.

title: quick golden stew
directions: In large saucepan, combine carrots, potatoes, onions and just enough water to cover.
Cook, covered, until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.
Add peas and ham.
Continue to cook 5 more minutes.
Drain water.
Stir in soup and cheese; heat through.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix soup, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, oil, mustard, onion and bell pepper.
Cook on low to dissolve sugar.
Continue cooking until onions and peppers are tender.
Pour while still hot over the drained carrots.
Store in covered dish in the refrigerator several hours or overnight prior to serving.

title: mississippi cornbread
directions: Mix well and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Place in dish in order.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: fish casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter or margarine.
Add flour and milk.
Cook to thicken.
To prepared sauce, add Cheddar cheese and prepared McCormick sour cream sauce.
Parboil fish, cool, skin and debone, if necessary.
Grease a casserole and put flaked fish into it with precooked peas.
Pour sauce mixture over fish and peas.
Bake 3/4 hour at 350° or until bubbly.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well and chill for several hours or overnight.

title: kasha varnishkas *
directions: Saute chopped onion in the oil until light brown.
Set aside. Mix the Kasha and egg whites.
Heat in a large pan, stirring constantly, until kernels become dry and separate.
Add the water and salt.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, over low heat until water is absorbed, about 10 to 15 minutes.
While Kasha is cooking, cook bow ties according to package directions.
Drain. Stir hot bow ties and sauteed onion into hot cooked Kasha.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: country fried apples
directions: Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until apples are tender. Uncover and cook for 10 minutes until juice is thick.

title: coconut-sour cream cake
directions: Bake cake in two layers.
Then split to make four layers. Bake cake by mix instructions.

title: risotto milanese
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
When hot, stir in rice. Continue stirring until pale gold in color.
Add onion.
Cook briefly and add 1 cup chicken stock.
Cover pan and cook slowly over low heat until liquid is absorbed, then add saffron that has been dissolved in white wine.
Add 2 1/2 cups hot chicken stock and mushrooms.
Cover and continue cooking until all liquid is absorbed and rice is fluffy.
Add butter and Parmesan cheese. Stir gently and serve.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix salt, sugar, pepper and flour.
Add well beaten egg, then stir in vinegar and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick. Cool and pour over slaw.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cover carrots with water.
Cook until tender.
Drain and return to pan.
Add preserves and butter.
Cook just until glazed.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburg and onion; drain grease.
Add sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer while noodles are cooking.
Mix together cottage cheese and eggs (beaten).
Mix together grated Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.

title: spuds ala elegant
directions: Blend cream cheese into potatoes.
Add other ingredients and mix to blend.
Bake in 1-quart casserole 45 minutes at 350°. Serve at once.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix until well blended Kraft dressing, Miracle Whip, pasta and fresh vegetables.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Coat chicken in flour and reserve leftover flour.
Brown chicken in oil and remove.
In oil stir in onions and flour and cook for 2 minutes.
Add water, bouillon, paprika, salt and pepper.
Stir and add chicken.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 25 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken from skillet and stir in sour cream.
Serve over egg noodles, spaetzle or hot cooked rice. Serves 4.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with salt, pepper and chopped onion.
Add pizza sauce, macaroni.
Top with pepperoni and cheese.
After putting in large casserole dish, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
You may add one can mushrooms to topping if you desire.

title: brickle bars
directions: Mix all ingredients well, then add the package of Bits 'O Brickle.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Butter 9 x 9 x 3 inch pan.
Heat sugar, milk, chocolate, corn syrup and salt in a 3 quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly until chocolate is melted and sugar is dissolved.
Cook stirring occasionally to 234° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add margarine.
Cool without stirring to 120° (bottom of pan will be lukewarm).
Add vanilla, beat constantly with wooden spoon until candy is thick and no longer glossy, about 5-10 minutes.
Mixture will hold its shape when dropped from spoon. Quickly stir in and spread into loaf pan.
Cut into 1 inch squares.

title: easy crab imperial
directions: Saute the green pepper and onions.
Mix all ingredients, except crackers and crabmeat, then add crabmeat.
Put into greased casserole or individual serving shells.
Top with mashed Ritz crackers and butter or margarine.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1/2 hour, until lightly browned.
Broil for about 1 to 2 minutes.

title: garlic spinach
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Melt oleo in saucepan.
Add onion and garlic.
Let simmer; do not brown.
Add spinach.
Stir in flour, then milk and cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Put in casserole; top with seasoned bread crumbs.
Brown in oven.
This is best when made a day before the meal.

title: mile high meringue
directions: Choose a dry, hot humid, day to make meringue.
Use only metal or glass bowls.
Plastic bowls can have a greasy film that can prevent foaming.
Separate the eggs carefully.
Be sure not even a bit of yolk gets in with the whites, because fat in the yolk can keep the foam from forming.
Separate the eggs while they are cold.
Let egg whites stand at room temperature for about 1/2 an hour after separating.
They will whip to greater volume than if beaten when cold.
Add 1/8 teaspoon cream of tartar for each egg white before beating.
Beat with electric mixer at high speed just until foamy.
Then gradually begin adding sugar, about 1 tablespoon at a time, beating as you slowly sprinkle the sugar in. Adding sugar too quickly can keep the foam from forming.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add all the remaining ingredients and blend with a wooden spoon.
