Put into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
Cut into squares.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Store in tightly sealed jar.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of boiling water.

title: cheesy chicken corn chowder
directions: In a saucepan, combine chicken, onion, celery and 1/2 cup water.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove chicken.
When cool enough to handle, cut off meat and chop.
Discard skins and bones.
Return meat to broth. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Oil bottom and sides of 8 x 10-inch ovenproof glass pan.
Wash cut chicken parts, preferably breasts or thighs.
Combine cream and mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° until tender.
Uncover and bake until brown, lightly.

title: cottage cheese cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water and add lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Whip cranberry sauce and add with cottage cheese and sour cream to gelatin.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch ring mold; chill until set.
(Unmold and fill center with cream cheese dressing.)

title: chicken breasts with cheese
directions: *You may substitute any white cheese.
Provolone is good.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put hamburger into large mixing bowl.
Add egg, Ragu sauce and brown sugar and mix.
Add Ritz crackers and mix well.
Put some Ragu sauce in bottom of baking dish.
Make a hamburg loaf and put it in baking dish.
Cover loaf with rest of sauce.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: easy supper pizza
directions: Cook ground beef in 10-inch skillet, stirring occasionally, until brown; drain thoroughly.
Stir in pizza sauce and 2 tablespoons flour.
Heat to boiling.
Boil and stir one minute. Pour into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheeses. With a fork, beat eggs, milk and 1 cup flour and green onions until blended.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until puffy and golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° for glass baking dish). Line a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with foil extended over the edges to form handles. Grease foil. Microwave chocolate and butter in large microwavable bowl on High for 2 minutes or until butter is completely melted. Stir sugar into chocolate mixture until well blended.
Spread into prepared pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Do not overbake; cool in pan.

title: date nut roll
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Make into rolls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in buttered casserole (9 x 13-inch).
Top with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes until brown.

title: no friller mystery crackers
directions: Put crackers in plastic bowl with lid.
Pour over oil and dry ingredients.
Stir gently every few hours with wooden spoon.
Do not refrigerate.
Enjoy anytime.
Ooh, it's so good!

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and put in pie shell.
Put rhubarb on top of the mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until done.
Take from oven.
Beat egg whites and add 3 tablespoons sugar and cream of tartar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: walnut muffins(lite)
directions: Coat a 12-cup muffin tin with nonstick spray or line the cups with paper baking cups.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, cream 2 tablespoons of the margarine, 1/4 cup of the brown sugar, the sugar and the applesauce.
Add the egg whites and beat until fluffy. Stir in the yogurt.
In a medium bowl, whisk the flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Whisk in 3 tablespoons of the walnuts.
Add the dry ingredients to the creamed mixture, stirring just enough to combine.
Spoon the muffin batter into the muffin tin, filling the cups 1/3 to 1/2 full.
Cream the remaining 2 tablespoons of margarine with the remaining brown sugar.
Stir in the remaining 1 tablespoon of chopped nuts.
Top each muffin with a sprinkling of the nut topping.
Bake at 400° until golden brown and a cake tester comes out clean when inserted in the center of a large muffin, about 18 minutes.
Cool the muffins on a rack.
Makes 18.

title: four corn tacos(contains 2 milligrams of fat)
directions: Heat chili.
Fix just like a taco.
Try with fat-free refried beans.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, milk and butter and pour into an 8 x 9-inch pan.
Bake
25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over cake and
then
nuts.	Pour caramel topping (heated and mixed with flour) over cake.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix together and press into bottom of pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain fruits; combine ingredients and chill overnight.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cool.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: spinach rice
directions: Brown onions and peppers in cooking oil.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Season to taste.
Pour into well oiled baking dish.
Bake in moderate over 375 degrees for 35 minutes. If desired 1/2 c. diced bacon may be substituted for cooking oil.

title: jerri's jumpin' juice
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator.
Drink 2 ounces per day and you'll be jumpin' like Jerri!

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In boiling water, cook zucchini and onion until well done. Drain completely and mash.
Add oil, grated Cheddar cheese, crushed soda crackers, beaten eggs, salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Put mixture into casserole dish and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: hungarian pork stew
directions: Mix flour, pepper and salt in pan. Dredge pork cubes in mixture.
Heat oil	in
large
skillet;
add garlic until tan. Add meat and
brown.
Remove meat and add veggies, saute until onions get limp
and
deglaze
with
beef stock and wine.	Add meat, tomatoes and
all spices.
Cover and cook on medium heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender.
Serve over noodles with a dollop of
sour cream or yogurt.
Invite Uncle Phil for supper.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring water to boil.
Pour rice in; cover and cook for 7 minutes.
Add milk and butter; stir.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add a little of the hot mixture to the egg mixture and then add this to the hot mixture.
Add the raisins.

title: night before scrambled eggs
directions: Beat 1/2 of the eggs at a time and scramble until soft stage. Put all eggs together.
Heat 2 cans mushroom soup, mushrooms and cheese until cheese is melted.
Put eggs into 9 x 13-inch pan; cover with soup mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika and refrigerate overnight.
One hour before serving, remove from refrigerator. Bake, covered, at 250° for 40 minutes and uncovered for 10 minutes.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat with the electric mixer for a full 5 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: creamsicle punch
directions: In large bowl, beat with electric mixer the eggs with honey yellow in color.
Stir in juices.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: baked bean and bacon casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain but reserve 2 tablespoons fat. Brown beef and onion in reserved fat.
Drain.
Set aside half the bacon for a topping and combine all ingredients in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix well.
Top with reserved bacon.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil all ingredients except popcorn and baking soda for 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Stir in soda very quickly.
Pour the caramel mixture over the popcorn and stir.
Put it in a roaster pan or other large pan in a 250° oven for one hour, stirring occasionally.
After it has cooled, store in a tight container.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Shape like an egg.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts in a pot. Melt butter. Put into baking dish. Put melted butter and stuffing together. Place 1/2 of it into a baking dish. Pinch up chicken (save chicken broth). Place on top of stuffing. Pour 1/2 of chicken broth over the chicken. Mix remaining stuffing, sour cream and soup together. Spread over chicken. Spoon the remaining chicken broth on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Fry diced bacon until crisp; remove from pot.
Drain off fat. Add onions and celery to remaining grease; fry until golden brown. Add tomatoes, catsup, garlic, bell pepper, okra, sauces and bay leaves.
Bring to a boil.
Add 1 pint boiling water; let cook slowly for an hour or more.
Add 2 tablespoons flour thickening; let simmer for a few minutes.
About 25 minutes before serving, add shrimp, salt and pepper.
Just before serving, add crisp bacon.
Serve with plain boiled rice.

title: golden feather cake
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl and beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour into pans or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost with your favorite frosting.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs, almond extract and vanilla.
Beat in flour.
Spread 3/4 of batter in a 9 x 12-inch greased, unfloured pan.
Next, spread cherries on top of batter.
Drop remaining 1/4 of batter on top of cherries by the teaspoonful.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes (until brown on top).

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Moisten eggplant (with milk) and coat lightly in flour. Quickly brown slices in hot oil, dusting each side with seasoned salt. When fork-tender and golden brown, transfer to 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Cover loosely with foil and bake at 375° about 20 to 25 minutes. Combine sauce, jelly and tomatoes with fork. Heat on medium until hot. Do not boil. Spread Mozzarella cheese over eggplant, then add sauce. Top with Parmesan and return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes to melt Mozzarella. Serve immediately.

title: sally muller's chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix in pot and bring
to
boil	the
butter,
cocoa and water. Pour over sugar and
flour
in
bowl.
Stir
well, add buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon
and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased cookie sheet and
bake
20 minutes at 400°.
Make icing 20 minutes before cake is done.

title: onion delight
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 4-inch casserole dish.
Slice onions thin. Layer onions, cheese and chips in dish, starting with onions.
Mix milk and soup; pour over onions, chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until onions are tender when pricked with fork.

title: grandma fleener's skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter and sugar.
Add eggs and dates in skillet; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts, Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Butter hands; roll into balls, then roll balls in powdered sugar or coconut.

title: 60-minute rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set about 15 minutes.
Make into rolls and let rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 425° until brown.
Brush with melted butter.

title: onion rings
directions: Combine all batter ingredients in small mixing bowl.
Stir until smooth.

title: cheese ball or roll
directions: Let cheeses soften; mix and add pecans and garlic or onion. Shape into balls or rolls.
Roll in some chipped pecans, parsley flakes or paprika.
Looks pretty to divide in thirds and roll in one of each.
These taste better prepared one day before serving.

title: eggplant oyster casserole
directions: Peel and cube and cook eggplant in water with a little onion juice; drain well.
Butter casserole dish and layer with cracker crumbs, eggplant and dot with margarine.
Salt and pepper.
Repeat and pour over the top a can of oyster stew; top with more crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cut crust from bread.
Put crust in a 9 x 9-inch pan (greased). Cover crust with broccoli (cooked and drained).
Put layers of ham, then layer of cheese slices on top.
Place bread square over cheese. Beat eggs, milk, onion and spices.
Pour this over bread. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over the top before baking.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and bake in graham cracker crust in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Take out and cool; add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 475° oven for 10 minutes.

title: ham noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed; drain.
In saucepan, over low heat, melt 2 tablespoons oleo in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until thick.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Add noodles and rest of ingredients.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with 1 tablespoon oleo and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until brown.
Serves four.

title: oatmeal butter cookies
directions: Mix all together and put on wax paper.
Roll into a log on wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut cookies about 1/4-inch thick and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.
They will be a light golden color.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan; cook over medium heat until marshmallows and butter melt, stirring often.
Cool 1 minute.
Combine popcorn and remaining ingredients in a large bowl; add marshmallow mixture, stirring until well blended.
Press about half of popcorn mixture into a greased 10-inch tube pan, packing well.
Press remaining popcorn mixture into pan.
Let set about 2 hours.
Invert popcorn cake from pan onto a cake plate. Yields one 10-inch cake.

title: pot pie
directions: Roll thin 1 large can and 1 small can of biscuits and line oblong pan (13-inch).
Add veggies and soup.
Sprinkle chicken on top.
Add crust and cut holes in biscuits like donut holes; it makes it pretty.
Cook at 350° until golden brown.

title: picnic stuffed eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise; remove yolks and set whites aside. In a small bowl, mash yolks with a fork.

title: cheese and tuna brunch bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease the 6 cups of a brunch pan or spray with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients thoroughly, then spoon into the 6 greased cups, dividing evenly.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool for 5 to 10 minutes, then loosen around edges with a knife and remove with a pancake turner.
Serves 6.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Pack firmly into an ungreased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: sliced zucchini pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar, salt and spices to boil, stirring until dissolved.
Pour over zucchini and onions and let stand for 1 hour.
Bring to boil and cook for 3 minutes.
Pack in pint jars. Process in water for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 -7 pints.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix well and bake in 350° oven.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Blend margarine and cream cheese.
Add chopped onion, mayonnaise and dash of salt and pepper.
Mash can of shrimp and blend with ingredients.
Set in mold or stuff celery.
Very good with just crackers.
Yummy.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Place the whole chicken in deep baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, basting several times with some reserved sauce.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: hidden valley ranch easy pasta salad
directions: Toss all ingredients in a large bowl and chill to blend flavors.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: party pops
directions: Mix brownie mix and put in a 12-inch pizza pan; bake for 30 to 35 minutes at temperature recommended on box.
Cool completely. Frost with white frosting mix, made bright orange with red and yellow food coloring.
Make a jack-o'-lantern face with candy corn and M&M's candy pieces.

title: speedy beef goulash
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and green pepper in skillet until brown.
Stir in salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Simmer, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add corn.
Heat through.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Add sugar and shortening to potatoes while hot.
Combine this to flour mixture and knead lightly until dough can be easily handled.
Bake at 425° in a preheated oven 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: mandarin orange jello
directions: Follow directions on package for Jell-O.
Place into a medium serving dish with oranges and place into refrigerator until set, 1 hour or make ahead of time and keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble 1/2 package Oreo cookies and spread on bottom of 2 or 3-quart Pyrex dish.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add pudding and milk.
Beat at medium speed until thick. Pour over Oreos.
Crumble remaining Oreos into pudding.
(I take a spoon and push them into the pudding.)
Top with Cool Whip. Garnish with a few Oreo crumbs.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Scrub zucchini well and slice crosswise (about 1/4-inch thick slices).
Makes about 4-quarts.
Slice onions thinly.
Makes about 1-quart.

title: mama's pork chop casserole
directions: Place sliced potatoes in a large baking dish or pan.
Mix soup and water and pour half over potatoes.
Salt pork chops and place on top of potatoes.
Place onion on top of pork chops.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour remaining soup mixture on top and cover. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until pork chops are tender.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon ends.
Saute onion and bell pepper in 3 tablespoons bacon grease in large skillet until tender.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook slowly, covered, for approximately 45 minutes. Sprinkle crumbled bacon ends on top and serve.
Serves 6.

title: crab cakes
directions: Crumble crackers.
Pour milk over crackers; let stand 10 minutes.
Beat 2 eggs with salt, pepper and parsley.
Mix lightly with two forks.
Add crab meat; mix lightly through and through. Make patties.
Fry in oil 1/4-inch deep on medium heat, browning on each side.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Mix browned meat, onion and 1/2 cup cheese; save remaining cheese for top.
Place 4 shells on bottom of oiled cake pan and layer remaining ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked spareribs
directions: Wipe with clean cloth the spareribs.
Cut into pieces.
Place in large roasting pan, meaty side up.
On each section place a slice of lemon and a slice of onion.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: freezer coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage; sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Heat sugar, vinegar, water, mustard and paprika; boil 1 minute.
Drain cabbage.
Put in large bowl.
Pour vinegar mixture over.
Add diced pimento or green pepper; mix well.
Divide among 3 (1-pint) freezer containers.
Cover, label and freeze up to 2 months.
This is delicious and easy.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Knead and roll out.
Makes 6 or more crusts.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Choose ripe, but firm, cling peaches.
Peel.
Make a syrup of sugar, vinegar and spices.
Boil 5 minutes.
Drop peaches into syrup and simmer for about 15 minutes or until tender.
Pack into clean, hot jars.
Pour syrup over peaches and seal.
Yields 4 pints.

title: tasty low-fat baked chicken
directions: Season chicken, potatoes and carrots with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Place in a large piece of aluminum foil sprayed with Pam.
Top with onion slices and margarine.
Fold foil shut. Bake at 425° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken or turkey tetrazzini
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, combine soup, water and cheese.
Heat to boil; stir occasionally.
Stir in spaghetti, meat, parsley and pimento.
Heat through.
Stir often.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut polka dot bars
directions: Lightly butter 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large saucepan over low heat, melt candy coating and peanut butter; blend well.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal and peanuts; mix well.
Press mixture evenly into prepared pan.
Immediately sprinkle chocolate pieces over bars, pressing lightly into surface.
Allow to set 45 to 60 minutes before cutting into bars.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: singapore supper
directions: Combine chicken, pea pods, carrots and green onion in large bowl.
Combine picante sauce, soy sauce, sesame oil and sugar; mix well.
Toss with chicken mixture; chill.

title: tex-mex-bagel chips
directions: In small bowl, thoroughly blend all ingredients, except bagels.
Brush both sides of bagels with mixture.
Bake at 250° on ungreased baking sheets, 50 minutes or until crisp.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine in bowl, stir well.
Put in can with tight lid.
Store 3 to 4 weeks before use.
Makes 2 cups bulk tea.
Use 1/2 teaspoon per cup.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Pour
all liquid off beans and mash. Add vanilla, eggs, margarine,	sugar
and
coconut. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350°
for
minutes.
Cool.
Serve
with
whipped cream, if desired.
You can use canned beans. This pie tastes like pecan pie.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 4 tablespoons sugar and melted butter.
Spread in a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip; spread on cooled crust. Dissolve jello in boiling water and add strawberries.
Chill until almost solid.
Spread on second layer.
Chill until set.

title: frozen peach salad
directions: Mix together pie filling, Eagle Brand milk and crushed pineapple.
Add lemon juice and almond extract.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Freeze.

title: fantastic dessert
directions: Slice cookies and place close together on cookie sheet.
Bake as directed.

title: stir-fried garlic shrimp
directions: Cook and stir garlic in oil, in nonstick skillet over medium-high heat for 1 minute.
Add shrimp; stir-fry 1 minute. Stir in mushrooms, onions and wine.
Stir-fry until shrimp are pink and vegetables are hot, about 2 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: molded ham salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
After Jell-O is partially congealed, add vinegar.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients and place in mold until firm.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix everything well.
Pour into mold or plastic bowl and freeze overnight.

title: lucille's peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together in saucepan.
Add cold water and peaches; stir over medium heat to dissolve sugar.
Let mixture come to a full rolling boil.
Boil 5 to 6 minutes, stirring.
Add butter and almond extract.
Place mixture in a 9 x 9-inch pan; cover with crust.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients lightly and shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake about 15 minutes on broiler pan in oven.
Put in sauce of choice.

title: baked round steak
directions: Lay steak on 2 large sheets of foil inside cake or casserole pan.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover with mushroom pieces. Cover and seal in foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Turn down to 300° for last half hour to keep it from getting dry. Serves 4.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix brown sugar, margarine, syrup and salt in saucepan and cook, stirring continually, over medium heat until it bubbles around edges, about 5 minutes.
Take off heat and stir in baking soda until foamy.
Pour batter into two medium or 1 large cake pan over the popped corn and stir well until coated.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour stirring every 15 minutes.
Put in covered container to store.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; reserve liquid.
Debone and cut into bite size pieces.
Layer chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together 3 cans of soup and 1 cup reserved chicken broth.
Pour over chicken, then mix together stuffing mix, 1 1/2 cups of reserved chicken broth and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Pour over soup mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and a golden brown, approximately 30 minutes.
Serves approximately 8 people.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Remove crust and place in 10 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Melt butter and cheese and pour over bread.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over cheese mixture and bread.
Let stand, covered with foil, overnight. Bake at 300° in hot oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Done when puffy and slightly brown.
Optional to add ham, mushrooms, onions and green pepper over entire mixture before baking.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add cake flour to creamed mixture, stirring just until blended. Stir in vanilla and orange extracts. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean. Let cake cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan; let cool completely on a wire rack. Yield: One 10-inch cake.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay bread on bottom of pan, you can make double layer.
Add milk to eggs, beat well, pour over bread. Spread meat evenly over bread and spread cheese evenly over meat. Cover with foil, refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: barbecue burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes, covered. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: In a covered boiler, cook rice in 2 1/2 cups plus 2 tablespoons of chicken broth for 20 minutes.
Add onion; cook for 5 minutes more.
Stir rice occasionally.
Add all other ingredients in rice and pour in large pan.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Mix soups.
Add Ro-Tel
and broth.
Add onion.
Heat to simmer.
Put layer of chips into 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with half the chicken.
Pour
half of soup mixture over chicken. Repeat.
Top with chips.
Sprinkle with Cheddar.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Great Mexican taste!

title: overnight green salad
directions: Shred lettuce, place in shallow 4-quart size dish.
Top with onion, celery and chestnuts.
Break apart frozen peas; sprinkle over greens.
Add mayonnaise, sugar, cheese, salt and garlic salt. Cover and chill in refrigerator overnight.
Before serving, slice boiled eggs and decorate salad.
Add crumbled bacon bits and tomatoes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: fruity mint punch
directions: Bring 4 cups water to boil.
Pour into heat resistant pitcher and add tea bags and mint.
Let stand 5 minutes and strain.
Stir in sugar, lemonade concentrate, limeade concentrate and 3/4 cup orange juice. Chill.
Place mixture in large punch bowl and stir in 3 quarts of cold water.

title: chili balls
directions: Mix ingredients into balls the size of an egg.
Make a sauce of tomatoes or tomato soup (dilute as directed) and add chili powder.
Drop balls into liquid and cook for 2 hours on low heat.

title: albacore fettucine
directions: In a large pot of water, cook broccoli until crisp-tender. Remove with a slotted spoon to serving bowl.
Add fettucine to same pot of water; cook until tender.
Drain and add to broccoli. Stir in albacore.

title: smoked salmon with dill dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve with tray of cut up vegetables.

title: scallops saute
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; add margarine.
Place over medium-high heat until margarine melts. Add peas and celery; saute 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp-tender. Remove vegetables from skillet, using a slotted spoon; set aside.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in large skillet with onion.
Add 5 cups water, bouillon, salt, paprika, garlic, mustard and mushrooms.
Cook until meat is tender.
Mix flour, cornstarch, water and sour cream.
Dip cup of hot mixture into cold.
Mix. Add back slowly to beef mixture.
Heat until bubbly.
Enjoy.

title: pot roast breckenridge
directions: Brown roast beef in butter in a large Dutch oven.
Add carrots, celery, onion and garlic to pan.
Cook until onion is limp.
Add mushrooms.
Combine 1/2 of the consomme with the wine, salt, pepper, paprika and capers.
Add to beef.
Cover and bake at 350° for two hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat to warm platter. Puree vegetables and combine flour with remaining consomme.
Cook all to thicken.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat but do not boil. Serve over the meat.

title: chocolate chip-peanut butter pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat first 5 ingredients until smooth, 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Sprinkle pie shell with chocolate chips.
Pour filling over chocolate.
Bake 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350° and continue baking until tester inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate overnight.
Serve at room temperature.

title: lemon nut cake
directions: Cream butter in mixer; add sugar gradually.
Mix baking powder with flour and sift.
Leave out about 1/2 cup to pour over fruit. Mix eggs one at a time to batter, then flour and extract.
Mix raisins and nuts in batter.
Grease large tube pan and bake at low 325° or lower 1 hour or longer until tested done.
Cook cake in oven with door open.
Keep in refrigerator before cutting.
This is the best cake for Christmas.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Cook and drain lasagne.
Cook and drain spinach.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, onion, egg and spinach together.
Mix tomato sauce, sugar, basil, oregano, garlic, salt and pepper.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add half and half and crackers, then squash.
Put mixture in greased casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: pecan sandy dessert
directions: Put half of cookie crumbs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put ingredients (except cookies and Cool Whip) in a large bowl and beat about 10 minutes.
Fold in a large container of Cool Whip. Pour on top of crushed pecan sandies and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top of filling and freeze.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring constantly, about 1 minute.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, pepper and seasonings.
Cook until sauce thickens, 5 to 8 minutes.
Transfer 1/2 of sauce to medium bowl, reserving remaining sauce; add chicken to bowl and mix thoroughly; set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, with fork, combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and 1 tablespoon drained pineapple juice.
Add chicken and remaining ingredients.
Toss well, cover and refrigerate.
To serve, arrange lettuce on plates, lightly pile salad on lettuce and garnish with fresh fruit in season.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together in bowl.
Add melted butter. Stir well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat.
Stir in milk and beat well.
Pour in pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: curried fruit compote
directions: Melt butter and stir in sugar and curry powder.
Drain fruits and arrange in layers or rows in casserole dish, reserving cherries and enough fruit for garnish.
Cover fruits in casserole with butter and brown sugar mixture.
Arrange fruits for garnish and cherries on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until fruit is bubbling and heated through.
Serve hot.

title: easy pralines
directions: Mix well in a heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir to a full boil, then slowly for 3 to 5 minutes, until mixture reaches soft ball stage.* Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cup pecans (broken).
Beat mixture until it begins to thicken, but still looks shiny.
Drop tablespoonful of mixture quickly onto waxed paper to form 3-inch pralines.
Let cool.
If mixture thickens and starts to lose its shine while dropping pralines, add a few drops of evaporated milk.
Makes about 18 pralines.

title: eggnog
directions: Separate eggs into large bowls.
Whip egg whites with 1/2 of the sugar to firm peaks.
Whip yolks with 1/2 sugar until thick and lemon colored.
Add all other ingredients (except egg whites) to yolks; mix very well.
(You can whip the cream, if you like.) Fold the whites into the mixture.
Leave small "chunks" of the meringue intact.

title: brownie frosting
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; cook until mixture forms soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine.
Let stand until cool.
Add vanilla; beat until of spreading consistency. Yields enough frosting to cover a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: holiday dressing
directions: Cook corn bread in 1 large skillet and crumble into fine pieces.
Add all other ingredients, mixing well.
Add broth from turkey wings.
Add chicken broth if needed to make dressing juicy enough.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 30 to 45 minutes or until desired consistency and brownness.
This dressing can be made weeks ahead and frozen.
Thaw and cook when needed.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add to beaten eggs and buttermilk that have been mixed together.
Beat well; add oil and bake on ungreased griddle.
Delicious.

title: pam's best marinade
directions: Whisk together.
Marinate any kind of steak overnight.
Great for chicken too.
Barbecue meat.

title: buttery caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in a large 3-quart glass container.
Cut half of the butter into small pieces.
Scatter over corn; set aside.

title: sauce for basting chicken or pork
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend well.
Baste chicken or pork on grill or in oven.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Saute okra and onion together; add tomatoes.
If using fresh tomatoes, add 1/4 cup of tomato sauce.
Cook for about 15 minutes.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix it all with mayo and a small container of sour cream.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Combine
in
order
given.
Dot filling generously with butter before putting on top crust.
Bake at 425° for about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: tea time tassies
directions: Mash all ingredients together with a fork until completely mixed. Take in hand, divide into 24 equal balls. Place in muffin pans to make crust.

title: kluski noodle hot dish
directions: Melt oleo; add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy jalapeno quiche
directions: In unbaked pastry shell, layer ham, bacon, Swiss cheese, Cheddar cheese, onion, tomato, jalapeno peppers and parsley. Combine eggs, mustard and sour cream.
Pour egg mixture into pastry shell.
Bake quiche at 450° for 30 minutes or until filling is set. Cover edge of pastry with foil to prevent excessive browning.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine in a large, heavy saucepan; heat to boiling.
Stir constantly about 5 minutes over medium heat or until mixture reaches soft ball stage (238°).
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Stir vigorously until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Yields 3 pounds.

title: pitlochio pudding
directions: In large bowl, mix pudding.
Stir pineapple and marshmallows. Stir all together good, then stir in whip cream.

title: cheesy chicken soup
directions: Dice the vegetables, then saute in butter.
Add water to steam.
Add soups and milk, V-8 juice, oregano and diced chicken. Simmer until heated through.
Freezes well.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mandarin orange pie(makes 2)
directions: Drain oranges and mix in all ingredients.
Put into 2 graham cracker crusts.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Sift flour and cocoa together.
Add sugar, well beaten eggs, then vanilla.
Melt margarine; add to mixture, along with nuts. Mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When cool, serve with whipped topping.

title: apple butter pie
directions: Mix all together just like you would a pumpkin pie. Put in unbaked pie shell.
Start at 400°, then turn down to 350°.
Cook slow until done.

title: creamy chocolate dip
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; add balance of ingredients.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: mustard glazed carrots
directions: Boil carrots 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Stir in sauce and cook 1 to 2 minutes more.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: potato lefsa
directions: Mix ingredients together; roll out 1 tablespoon at a time, using flour to keep from sticking.
Roll thin.
Cook lightly on both sides on a griddle.
Cool on dish towel, keeping lefsa separated from each other by a piece of wax paper.
I put in about 1 1/2 cups flour and when I knead in flour I put a small round ball of dough and work in more flour until it rolls thin without sticking to the board.

title: montreal peppered steak marinade
directions: Combine oil, soy sauce and Montreal steak seasoning in glass dish; add steak.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Remove steak from marinade; discard marinade.
Grill or broil steak to desired doneness.
(You can also make beef kabobs by chopping beef into cubes prior to marinating.
Alternate beef cubes with pineapple chunks on skewers.)

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs and fruit cocktail.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Add brown sugar and coconut on top of batter. Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Blanch cabbage head in boiling water until leaves can be removed without breaking.
Cool head of cabbage under running water and peel off 12 leaves (6 servings, 2 leaves per cabbage roll).
With sharp knife, cut through tough bottom vein an inch or two or remove.

title: ruby fulp's icebox rolls
directions: Scald buttermilk.
Add sugar, salt, soda and melted shortening.
Cool to lukewarm and stir in yeast.
Add flour and knead to soft dough.
If you use it at once, let rise to double in bulk.
Can be used as rolls or as loaf.
Cook rolls in moderate oven.
If the dough is not used at once, place in icebox and use later.

title: quick raspberry coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Oil an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Blend milk, yogurt and brown sugar; add biscuit and baking mix.
Stir just to moisten mix.

title: pineapple chiffon pie
directions: Beat the egg and sugar well.
Add juice.
Let come to boil 1 minute or longer.
Pour over jello and mix.
Let cool until thickened but not fully set.
Whip cream until thick.
Fold in jello mixture.
Pour into 10-inch wafer crust.
Chill and store in freezer.
Let set out a few minutes before cutting.

title: carrot tea loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray loaf pan with Pam.
In a large mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients and blend.
Stir in remaining ingredients together; add to dry ingredients and beat only until well mixed.
(Batter is very thick.) Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour until golden brown and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Turn loaf out onto rack to cool.

title: moist banana bread
directions: Mash bananas and sugar together. If you prefer a caramel flavor, use brown sugar. Add the rest of the ingredients by hand (not mixer). Add butter last. You may include either 1/2 cup nuts, chopped or 1/2 cup butterscotch chips. Be sure to grease and/or spray pan. Bake in loaf pan in a 350° oven for approximately 1 hour. Check with toothpick in middle.

title: earthquake cake
directions: In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, put nuts and coconut.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box and pour over nuts and coconut. Melt cream cheese and margarine together.
Add 1 box confectioners sugar and mix well.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream oleo and oil together.
Beat in sugar.
Add beaten egg, then vanilla and sifted dry ingredients.
Chill one hour.
Make into small balls and press with fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 350° oven for about 12 minutes.
Chopped pecans can be added.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: cranberry glazed pork roast
directions: In a saucepan mix all ingredients except pork.
Cook until thick.
Place pork in a shallow baking pan.
Roast in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Spoon half of glaze over pork.
Continue roasting for 30 to 45 minutes or until internal thermometer reaches 155° to 160°.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
Serve with remaining sauce.
Serves 16.
Very easy, pretty and delicious.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: Blend with mixer, sugar, vinegar, oil, water, paprika, and salt.
Mix with vegetables and let set 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: shepherds pie
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with drained corn.
Prepare potatoes and spread on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are slightly browned.

title: finger salad
directions: Lay crescent rolls out flat in a greased cookie sheet, pressing seams together.
Bake as directed on package.
Cool. Blend dressing, sugar, cream cheese and mayonnaise together with mixture and spread on cooled crust.
Next top with cut up vegetables and press into crust.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese. make this ahead, perhaps the night before and chill.
Cut into squares.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed; beat for 3 minutes on high speed.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool.

title: cheese and mushroom quiche
directions: Prepare pie crust.
Cover crust with grated cheese.
Saute chopped onion, mushrooms and pepperoni in butter with salt, pepper and dash of thyme.
Cover cheese layer with sauteed mixture.
Beat together eggs, milk, flour, salt and dry mustard to make a custard.
Pour custard over mushroom layer.
Place broccoli chunks in custard.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until solid in center when jiggled.

title: orange-lemon salad
directions: Dissolve jellos in boiling water; cool.
Put in lemon pie filling.
Drain mandarin oranges and save the juice.
Add water to make 1 cup.
Add oranges and juice.
Mix.
Pour in jello mold and chill overnight.

title: party mints
directions: Mix and knead as for pie dough.
Add more powdered sugar if needed.
Add flavor and color and mix in with hands.
Roll in small balls, then roll in small amount of granulated sugar so they won't stick to molds.
Place in mold and press lightly.
Unmold on waxed paper.
Makes 60.
You can freeze these if you want.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add any salt and pepper sparingly. Split buns.
Spread mixture on bottom halves.
Put top halves in place and wrap each burger in foil.
Heat on baking sheet in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
If ripe olives are omitted, add more cheese.
Makes six servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the sugar, cornstarch and salt in large saucepan. Gradually stir in evaporated milk and water.
Add chocolate.
Cook and stir over medium heat until chocolate is completely melted and mixture boils.
Boil 1 minute; remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill pie at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve topped with meringue or whipped topping.

title: scootin' long-the-shore
directions: Cook slowly all ingredients until tender.
Serves 4.

title: chipped ham barbecue sandwiches
directions: Cook onion in shortening over medium heat until soft but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients except ham.
Mix thoroughly. Bring to boiling point, then simmer 10 minutes.
Add chipped ham and heat.
Makes 8 sandwiches.

title: egg salad triangles
directions: Combine eggs, olives and green onion. Stir in mayonnaise and mustard.
Remove crusts from bread, if desired. Spread each slice of bread with 1/4 cup of the egg mixture.
Cut each slice of bread diagonally into quarters.
Makes 20 sandwiches.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Run the ham or the lunch meat and the Cheddar cheese through the food chopper, then mix the balance of the ingredients with the ham and Cheddar cheese.

title: duck a la'mandarin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prick duck skin all over and rub skin and cavity with salt and pepper.
Roast for 1 3/4 hours, or meat thermometer registers 180°.
Pour off fat about every 20 minutes.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pecan turtles
directions: Melt kisses and water in double boiler.
Add pecans.
Mix and lay in clusters on waxed paper.
Melt Hershey bars, milk chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip clusters in this mixture and lay on waxed paper until cool.

title: vegetable bars
directions: *Add any vegetable you like (broccoli, cauliflower, tomatoes, green pepper, grated carrots, mushrooms, black olives or green onions).

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients into blender jar.
Blend on high speed until smooth and foamy. Makes 6 cups.

title: ranch-mustard dip
directions: In food processor or blender, puree pimientos.
Add dressing and mustard; mix until creamy.
Transfer the mixture to a medium bowl.
Combine yogurt and sour cream.
Mix well.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serve with vegetables or chips or as a sauce for chicken or fish.

title: fun punch
directions: Add all ingredients to a gallon jug.
Can add more water if necessary to fill jug.
Add 1 1/2 quarts (48 ounces) 7-Up just before serving.
Any color of Kool-Aid can be used.
Great for birthday parties for little kids.

title: karen trelstad's corn bread
directions: Bake in 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with butter and honey.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well and place in buttered casserole dish; bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Add shredded cheese on top and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Melt fat in saucepan over low heat. Blend flour, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat until smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat. Stir in chicken broth and milk. Replace on heat and bring to boil. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Mix sauce with remaining ingredients. Pour into greased oblong baking dish. Bake 40 to 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: diet apple salad
directions: Mix altogether and serve chilled.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs all together.
Add bananas which have been mashed.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to blended banana mixture.
Add nuts and blend.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until dissolved.
Bring to a boil, then cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.
Pour very quickly into greased pan. Cool and cut into squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: blitz torte
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk.
Divide batter; put into 2 layer pans.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Add 1 cup sugar; spread over batter in pans.
Cover with nuts.
Bake in a slow oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; turn one layer upside down on plate. Cover with pudding, then place other layer, nut sprinkled side up.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits according to package.
After cooking grits, add 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Add eggs and pepper.
Mix well.

title: dr. pepper salad
directions: Take 16 ounces of Dr. Pepper and heat. Dissolve the Jell-O with it, then beat with a fork and add the other 16 ounces of Dr. Pepper. Add pineapple and pecans.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.
If desired, sprinkle with parsley or paprika.
Serve with party breads.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Combine ground chuck, rice, onion, salt, pepper and egg; mix well.
Roll in cabbage leaves that have been dropped into boiling water for two minutes and drained.
Cover with diced tomatoes and juice or tomato soup.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake until hot at 375°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar and beaten eggs.
Dissolve the baking soda in 4 tablespoons hot water.
Mix alternately with flour and salt.
Lastly, add the chopped nuts, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except for pecans, and chill overnight.	Form into ball and then roll in pecans.

title: pickled carrot sticks
directions: Scrape carrots and cut into 3-inch lengths.
Simmer in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Cut into thin strips.
Combine sugar, vinegar, water and mustard seed.
Tie stick cinnamon and whole cloves in cheesecloth bag.
Add to the liquid mixture. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour over carrot sticks and cool.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove cheesecloth bag.
Drain and serve.
Reserve liquid to store with any leftover carrots.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Slice cucumbers longways; remove seed and grind cucumber coarse.
Add salt.
Grind peppers and onions; mix well and let stand overnight.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetable mixture.
Bring to boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes. Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: To make meatballs, combine beef, evaporated milk, oats, cracker crumbs, eggs, onion, garlic powder, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Place meatballs in a single layer on wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Freeze until solid. Store frozen meatballs in freezer bags until ready to cook.

title: hamburger stuffed bread
directions: Cut top off bread and hollow out loaf.
Tear bread into bite-sized pieces.
Brown beef.
Mix soup, celery, green pepper and seasonings; add to beef.
Stir well and simmer for 5 minutes. Add pieces of bread and mix well.
Fill bread shell and top with cheese slices.
Place on a cooking sheet and bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Cover with loaf top.
Slice and serve.

title: peachie cinnamon whirligigs
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine peaches (with syrup) and cornstarch in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Keep hot, stirring occasionally.
Stir baking mix, 2 tablespoons sugar, 2 tablespoons melted butter and the milk to a soft dough.
Gently smooth dough into a ball on well-floured cloth covered board. Knead 8 to 10 times.
Roll dough into 9-inch square, spread with 2 tablespoons butter.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and the cinnamon, sprinkle over square.
Roll up, seal well by pinching edge of dough into roll.
Pour peach mixture into square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Cut roll into 1-inch slices.
Place slices cut side up on hot peach mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm and if you like with cream.
Yields 9 servings.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla.
Fold in apples, walnuts and coconut. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tested and done.

title: cornmeal gravy
directions: Put bacon grease in skillet.
Add cornmeal.
Brown in skillet, stirring constantly.
Add milk, stirring, until thick.
Serve over meat.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix and form into ball.
Roll ball in chopped walnuts (optional).
Wrap and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: bacon and cheese quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate (or square pan).
Layer in pan onion, cheese and bacon (in that order).
Mix first five ingredients in bowl on high speed for one minute.
Pour over ingredients in pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil, vanilla and zucchini.
Beat together.
Beat dry ingredients into mixture; stir in nuts.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes in three loaf pans.

title: ultimate death by chocolate
directions: Follow directions on cake mix; bake and cool.
Make pudding and let cool.
In large bowl, layer cake, pudding and Cool Whip on top; add the Reese's pieces or whatever variation.
Use your imagination.
Cool in fridge.

title: swiss chocolate squares
directions: Combine water, margarine and chocolate in saucepan; bring to boil; remove from heat. Stir in combined flour, sugar, salt and soda. Add eggs and sour cream; mix well. Pour into greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Frost cake while warm. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: grandma turner's "old fashion" jam cake*
directions: Mix sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, jam, fruit and buttermilk (roll raisins in some of the flour) and mix all spices, flour and raisins in batter.
Stir well.
Pour into 2 large pans, well-greased and floured.
Bake slowly until well done in 350° oven.
Cool in
pans for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost with caramel icing.
Best made ahead for about 3 to 5 days for moisture.
Great frozen!

title: chinese spareribs
directions: Rub ribs well with other ingredients.
Let stand overnight to marinate well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour on rack.
Baste with sauce the last 20 minutes.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients into the small mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Form into ball and press firmly onto sides and bottom of 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Mix with sugar and nuts.
Mix orange juice and butter.
Mix wafer mixture to orange juice mixture. Form small balls and roll in coconut.
Yields about 100.

title: chocolate chews
directions: Cream together the eggs, the sugar and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Melt and cool the bitter chocolate and margarine. Then add it to the sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add the flour to the mix.
Bake in a greased 11 x 7-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut.

title: vanilla cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Add the rest; mix well. Bake at 375° until light brown, for 6 to 10 minutes.

title: tacos
directions: Saute beef in a 10-inch skillet until it loses redness.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in taco seasoning and Manwich.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 16 tacos.

title: slush
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Freeze until solid and mix with 7-Up (about 1/2 and 1/2).

title: marinade for meat
directions: Place all ingredients in blender 30 to 40 seconds.
Marinate meat for 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Also use for basting.
Good for roasts, chops and large cubes of beef for shish kabobs.

title: mississippi delta cornbread
directions: Mix, starting with top ingredients all the way down.

Pour into 2 small square pans for thick bread or 3 medium size long casserole dishes which have been greased well with solid Crisco. Bake on top shelf at 350° if pans are glass or at 375° if pans are thick metal.
Bake from 30 to 40 minutes.
Watch.

title: rolls
directions: Mix 1 cup warm water, 2 tablespoons sugar and yeast; let set. Mix rest of ingredients and add yeast mixture; knead about 6 to 10 minutes. Put in greased bowl and let rise until double in size. Punch down; roll about 1/2-inch in thickness. Cut with biscuit cutter. Place in greased pan; let rise until double in size. Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fresh christmas eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks in bowl until smooth.
Combine egg yolks and sugar in top of double boiler over hot water.
Stir in milk gradually.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture coats spoon. Remove from heat.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites and whipping cream into chilled egg yolk mixture.
Stir in rum flavoring.
Chill for several hours to blend flavors.
Stir in vanilla just before serving; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Yield:
24 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: cinnamon apple jelly
directions: Wash fruit; do not pare or core.
Cut in eighths, removing blemishes.
Barely cover with water; simmer until soft.
Strain juice through jelly bag.
Measure 4 cups of juice into large kettle.
Add sugar; stir until dissolved.
Bring to a full boil over heat.
Boil hard until syrup sheets off spoon, about 8° above boiling point of water.
Remove from heat.
Skim off foam quickly. Add cinnamon and coloring.
Pour into scalded glasses.
Seal immediately with paraffin.
Makes three 1/2-pint glasses.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Whip the 2 ingredients together.
Makes a real good dip for fresh fruit.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in refrigerator.
Can be used on potato salad, cabbage salad and lettuce salad.

title: lois' turkey stuffing
directions: Mix potatoes, bread cubes, eggs, butter, onion, celery and seasonings.
Add milk until moist but not too wet.
Place in buttered casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.
Take cover off for last 10 minutes.

title: chicken rice roger
directions: Brown chicken with flour.
Put rice, salt and pepper in greased casserole and add onion.
Put mushroom juice in it and add chicken and
pour
bouillon
over
all.
Dot
with butter. Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Dissolve both packages of jello in water.
Add remainder of ingredients and stir well.
Pour into mold and chill in refrigerator until firm.
Unmold and garnish with lettuce.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cream cheese pull-aparts
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
In a small bowl, combine cream cheese, parsley flakes, dill weed, garlic powder and hot cooked sausage and mix well.
Unroll dough into two long rectangles. Spread with Creamy Italian dressing.
Then spread mixture evenly over each rectangle.
Roll up, jelly roll style, pinching edges to seal.
Place sections together on cookie sheet, forming long roll.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Mix and pat in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: applesauce dessert
directions: Sprinkle the applesauce with cinnamon. Mix the flour, sugar, margarine and milk and pour over applesauce. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked sausage, cabbage and apples
directions: Pat out 8 flat sausages.
Brown until almost done.
Remove from skillet and add next 3 ingredients to fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Alternate layers of cabbage and apples in a 3-quart casserole.
Season each layer with salt, pepper and nutmeg. Arrange sausage patties on top and pour vinegar mixture over meat. Cover and bake about 45 minutes in oven at 375°.

title: potato skins
directions: Cut baked potatoes lengthwise.
Scoop out middle, leaving 1/4 to 1/3-inch potato remaining in shell.
Save middle for another recipe.
Quick fry potato skins.
Remove and drain.
Place 1/2 slice cheese in each skin and melt under broiler or in microwave. Top with bacon bits or fresh fried crumbled bacon.
Serve with sour cream and chives.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients in a small bowl until smooth. Top with nuts.
Serve with apple wedges.

title: chocolate layer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs; beat well.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour just enough batter (about 2 large spoonfuls) to cover the bottom of a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 375 degrees about 10 minutes.
Recipe should yield 12-14 layers.
Cake does not have to be cool to frost. "This cake is labor intensive but well worth the work."

title: spinach egg noodles with cream sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour; mix to paste.
Add milk and salt; stir over low heat until creamy.
Cook noodles as directed on package; drain and place in casserole.
Pour cream sauce over noodles and heat in moderate oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired, and serve hot.

title: haystacks
directions: Cook rice in boiling water for 20 minutes (until tender). Cook beans in microwave for 3 minutes.
Cut up tomatoes and tear up lettuce.

title: 3-bean bake
directions: Brown top 3 ingredients, then add remaining 9 ingredients with top 3.
Put into a casserole dish.
Bake together for 1 hour at 375°.

title: fried chicken of arles
directions: Cut up the chicken and brown the pieces on all sides in hot oil.
Remove chicken and deglaze the pan by pouring the wine into it and, with a wooden spoon over medium heat, rubbing down all the good brown substances into the liquid in the skillet.
Then add the tomatoes and garlic.
Simmer until this sauce is somewhat reduced.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: baked beans
directions: For each large can of Bush's baked beans, add catsup, brown sugar, Coca-Cola and diced onions.	Cook slow on stove top, uncovered, for 4 to 6 hours, stirring often.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine; add powdered sugar, flour, flavoring and eggs.
Blend well with mixer.
Pour in greased tube pan and bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare jello.
Add cranberries and sugar.
Cool, then add pineapple and marshmallows.
When jello is near setting, add whipped cream.
Chill for several hours.

title: sue's chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In large bowl, have oats, peanut butter and vanilla; set aside.
Spread on wax paper.

title: rusty's favorite peanut butter candy
directions: Mix well.
Roll into balls and then into more 4x sugar.
Serve to boys and girls.

title: orange balls
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll in balls and then roll in the remaining coconut.

title: shrimp and cheese casserole
directions: Break bread in small pieces.
Break cheese into bite size pieces.
Arrange shrimp, bread and cheese in several layers in greased casserole.
Pour margarine over this mixture.
Beat eggs. Add mustard and salt to eggs, then add milk.
Mix together.
Pour this over ingredients in casserole.
Let stand a minimum of 3 hours, preferably overnight in refrigerator, covered.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, covered.
Serves 4.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough water to hold together.
Roll into balls.
Bake on cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 325°.
May freeze.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: hungarian chicken or pork
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper together.
Dip chicken or pork into seasoned flour and brown in shortening.
Remove excess fat.
Lay chicken or pork in baking pan.
Sprinkle onion over meat.
Heat soup, thyme and water.
Pour over meat.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: ugly cake
directions: Mix the first three ingredients with hands and put in bottom of oblong cake pan.
Beat the remaining ingredients good and pour over first layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set and brown.

title: con queso
directions: Cook onions in margarine.
As they are cooking, add flour to milk, then add onions.
As it is simmering, cut up Velveeta in small chunks.
Add to milk and onions for thickness.
You may want to add more cheese, depending on how thick you want it. When done, add picante sauce.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil all except eggs together.
Shell hard-cooked eggs and place in hot jar (2-quart works well), covering with boiling liquid.
You can also place a whole red pepper in each jar.
Cover and let stand 2 or 3 days before eating.

title: easy moo shu pork(for diabetics)
directions: Thinly slice pork. Lightly spray large nonstick skillet with cooking spray. Heat over medium-high heat. Add pork and green onions. Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes or until pork is no longer pink. Stir in hoisin or Asian plum sauce. Stir in cole slaw mix. Spoon pork mixture onto tortillas. Wrap to enclose. Serve immediately. Makes 2 servings.

title: spoon bread
directions: Melt about 1/2 stick butter or margarine and pour into baking dish; tilt dish to coat bottom and set aside.
Sift all the dry ingredients together and gradually add the boiling water, stirring constantly.
Beat the eggs until they are light and add to mixture.
Stir in the buttermilk and pour batter into prepared dish.
Set the dish in a pan of water and bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli with pasta and garlic
directions: Steam broccoli.
Drain and set aside.
Cook pasta, drain and set aside.

title: weight watchers candy bar
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and then mix with remaining ingredients.
Shape into 2 logs.
Wrap with aluminum foil and freeze.

title: festive cake
directions: Mix and sift flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Stir in almonds.
Beat eggs slightly and combine with oil, almond extract, bananas and undrained pineapple.
Add to dry ingredients. Mix thoroughly but do not beat.
Spoon into well-oiled 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Bring to boil and boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, stir until melted.
Add
vanilla and oatmeal.
Stir well and drop onto wax paper.

title: crunchy tomato and chile salsa
directions: Coarsely chop the tomatoes.
Let stand in colander while preparing the other vegetables.
Coarsely chop the onions and peppers.
Mix drained tomatoes, onions and chile peppers with the salt, pepper and vinegar.
Pack mixture in clean hot jars (pint) to within 1/2-inch of top.
Process 15 minutes.
Keeps fresh up to a month in the refrigerator.
You may omit the black pepper and add 1 bunch chopped cilantro.

title: pizza dolce(italian cheese cake)
directions: Make crust like pie crust, roll out and fit to a roasting or lasagna pan.
Grease pan lightly and lay in crust.

title: broccoli balls
directions: Mix all together.
Form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk; mix well.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut out biscuits and cook in a greased pan in a 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Brush with melted butter on top of cooked biscuits.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a large baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Sift together dry ingredients and combine with milk.
Pour over butter. Do not stir.
Place peaches with syrup on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Shortly before serving time, combine in the punch bowl the chilled pineapple juice and 1 cup lemon juice.
Add the strawberries and their syrup.
Stir to blend thoroughly.
Add the chilled ginger ale and blend.
Add ice cubes or molded ice block.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Cream until smooth.
Chill 1 hour.
Press into greased mini-tins; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients mixing well.
Spoon into pastry shells.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool and serve.
Yield 2 doz.

title: jello dessert
directions: Set out sherbet to soften slightly.
In bowl mix jello and boiling water, stir to dissolve.
Add sherbet and Cool Whip.
Put in container with oranges.
Layer jello first, then oranges, then jello again.
Finish off with oranges and top with ground nuts, if you wish.

title: party mix with white chocolate
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Melt chocolate by package directions.
Pour white chocolate over mixture in bowl and stir. Then spread mixture out on wax paper to dry.
After dry, break into pieces and put into container.

title: stuffing
directions: Slightly beat eggs.
Add other ingredients, one at a time. Mix thoroughly.
Add salt and pepper.
Place in greased dish and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
May use to stuff turkey or roasting chicken.

title: peanut butter clusters
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat; add butter and peanut butter.
Stir well.
Pour mixture over cereal.
Mix well.
Drop spoonfuls onto wax paper. Let cool and serve.

title: prudence island quahaug chowder
directions: Cover
quahuags
with
water
and bring to a boil. When open, remove from shell and chop.
Saute diced onion in olive oil.
Add quahaug
juice, diced potatoes, parsley and chopped quahaugs. Cook until potatoes are done.
Add hot milk or milk mixture.
Dab of
butter may be added, when serving.
Makes 6 large servings.

title: kansas dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and spread one half of crumbs evenly in a 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Mix cream cheese and butter together with an electric mixer until smooth.
Mix in confectioners sugar.
Fold in whipped topping.
In a separate bowl, mix together pudding mix, milk, and vanilla.
Fold cream cheese mixture into pudding mixture and pour into pan over cookie crumbs.
Sprinkle the remaining cookie crumbs over the top.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken; remove from bones and cut in chunks.
Cook spaghetti in chicken stock.
Melt fat in skillet; add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted. Combine all.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Prepare pumpkin as for pies (2). Pour into a 9 x 13 pan or a 10 x 14. Sprinkle cake mix over top of filling. Slice butter over cake mix. Sprinkle nuts on top. Bake for 40 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: chicken breasts in mushroom sauce(microwave)
directions: Combine mushrooms and onions in 1-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain well.
Place margarine in 4-cup measure.
Microwave on High until melted. Blend in flour.
Add sherry, water, yogurt, salt, pepper and bouillon.
Stir in mushrooms and onions.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Set aside 2/3 cup of yellow cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix, margarine and beaten egg.
Stir by hand until mixture is crumbly.
Press the mixture evenly over the bottom and pinch up sides of an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: polenta for microwave
directions: In a small saucepan over low heat, mix together water and sugar.
Boil over low heat until mixture is clear.
Stir to dissolve sugar occasionally.
Remove from heat and cool slightly. Dip the crocheted doily in warm water, then roll it in a bath towel to absorb as much water as possible.
Next, dip the doily in the sugar-starch solution, saturating it completely.
Remove doily and stretch it to the desired shape on a towel or covered piece of cardboard.
Can use pins to hold to shape with the cardboard.
Let dry.
If doily has ruffles, stand small glasses between ruffles as they dry.

title: baked crab meat
directions: Cream the shortening and flour.
Cook the milk and American cheese until thick, stirring constantly.
Add the other ingredients.
Cover with crumbs and bake in a casserole for 10 minutes at 400°.
Serves six.

title: onion cake
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon; drain and cook onion in margarine. Combine sour cream, flour and salt.
Add eggs.
Stir in bacon and onions.
Pat crescent dough into greased 9-inch square pan.
Pour onion mixture over dough.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: holly's christmas punch
directions: Mix together; chill in freezer until partially frozen.
Stir to evenly distribute ice crystals and unfrozen punch.
Serve over ice cubes.

title: mom's popovers(makes 8 popovers)
directions: Mix together the flour and salt.
Whisk the eggs with the milk. Gradually whisk the liquid into the dry ingredients until smooth and well blended.
Let the batter rest for 1 hour.

title: mexican sandwich
directions: In small bowl, combine avocado dip and cream cheese; blend well.
Spread each tortilla evenly with avocado mixture to within 1/2 inch of edge.
Arrange slices of meat, lettuce, cheese and sprouts over avocado mixture.
Spoon on desired amount of salsa. If sandwiches are made ahead, omit salsa and spoon onto portions just before serving.
Roll up each tortilla; secure with toothpick.
Serve immediately or wrap securely in plastic wrap and refrigerate until serving.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package.
Saute pepper and onion in butter until soft.
Puree tomatoes in blender and add to pepper and onion.
Add crawfish and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add soup and rice.
Put mixture in a buttered casserole dish and top with slices of cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix together and cook on hot slightly greased griddle.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in a 2-quart bowl.
Stir in strawberries, pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Pour half the mixture into a 9 x 9-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread with sour cream.
Top with remaining gelatin mixture.
Chill until firm.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: football party dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with party dip.
Stir in red bell peppers, black olives and chillies.
Chill an hour.
Using spatula, form a football shape on platter.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Let frozen orange juice and lemonade thaw.
Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice, thawed orange juice and lemonade.
Puree bananas in blender.
Add to liquid.
Mix well. Freeze (at least 3 hours; can be made several weeks ahead). Remove from freezer 30 to 40 minutes before serving.
Place in punch bowl.
Add 3 bottles of lemon-lime drink.
You can use an ice ring or serve over ice cubes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in about 1 cup of water until just tender.
Add butter, onions, sour cream and soup.
Put large chunks of stuffing in casserole and crumbs on the top.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: cream of oyster stew
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart saucepan.
Saute celery, onion and carrots in melted butter for 5 minutes.
Add white pepper and liquor that has been drained from oysters.
Add mushroom soup and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Heat to low simmer.
Add parsley and oysters.
Heat until oysters are plump and edges begin to ruffle. Serve immediately.
Add a splash of sherry before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ham and rice stir-fry
directions: Cook Success rice according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Saute onions and celery in oil until tender-crisp. Add mushrooms, peas, olives and Hormel chunk ham; cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Push mixture aside in pan and scramble eggs.
Add rice and soy sauce.
Toss lightly with ham and rice mixture until completely heated.
Garnish with mandarin orange slices and celery leaves, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups warm water.
Melt butter and cream with sugar in large bowl, then add beaten egg.
Add dissolved yeast to cream mixture, then add flour and stir until mixed.
Place in airtight bowl and store in refrigerator.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Add well beaten eggs. Add flour, milk and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: tasty potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes generously with water.
Bring to a boil and lower heat to medium.
Add celery, onion, salts and pepper and simmer 15 minutes.
Add milk and heat through well.
While soup is simmering, melt butter and stir in flour for thickener.
Add to soup to thicken, stirring until desired consistency.

title: aunt delores' wet burritos
directions: Mix taco mix with water.
Cook hamburger meat.
Mix stewed tomatoes.
Combine refried beans, peppers and cheeses and pour this in with hamburger mixture.
Fill soft taco shells inside and roll up.
Put some meat mixture on top and add cheese.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Saute onion, bacon and ground beef until brown; drain.
Add catsup, brown sugar, vinegar, dry mustard and salt.
Add the beans to meat mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into lightly greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry cream freeze
directions: Place cream cheese in a bowl; mash with a fork.
Add berries and sugar; mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into foil lined muffin tins.
Freeze until firm, about 2 hours.
Makes 12 servings.

title: overnight vegetable salad
directions: Layer these ingredients in salad bowl, in order listed. Spread the following dressing over top.
Cover with plastic wrap, sealing edges.
Serve the next day.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
In a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine the chili, enchilada sauce, tomato sauce, 1 cup sharp cheese and the Fritos.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cannelloni and chicken with ham
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a frying pan, melt 4 tablespoons of butter.
Add chicken breasts and fry for 5 minutes, until lightly browned on both sides.
Transfer to bowl.
Add chicken livers to the frypan and cook 2 minutes on each side.
Transfer to bowl with chicken breasts.
Mince the chicken breasts, livers and ham together.
Add 1/4 cup Parmesan to the ground meat and mix well with a fork.
In a medium saucepan, melt another 4 tablespoons butter.
With a wooden spoon, stir the flour into the butter and cook for 2 minutes.
Remove the pan from the heat and stir in the milk slowly.
Return to heat and cook until sauce thickens.
Remove and add cream, salt and pepper.
Add 1/4 of the sauce to the meat and cheese mixture in the bowl and mix well.
Set aside.
Bring 2 1/2 quarts of water to a boil.
Drop into the boiling water and cook for 6 to 15 minutes, depending on the thickness.
With a slotted spoon, remove the pasta from the pan and place on dampened cloth to drain.
Using 1 tablespoon of butter, grease a large baking dish and spread 2 tablespoons of meat and cheese mixture on each pasta square.
Fold over and make a roll.
Place the cannelloni in either one or two layers, placing the joined side down in the baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and cover with reserved sauce.
Dot the top of the dish with small pieces of butter and place in oven.
Bake for 30 minutes until lightly browned.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Drain fruit (save 1 cup of juice).
Mix instant pudding, Tang and 1 cup juice.
Mix well.
Add fruit to pudding and refrigerate for 3 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crab and shrimp casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients except chips. Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with chips.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs.
Add oleo, salt and vanilla; continue beating.
Add buttermilk, cocoa, flour and baking soda.
Add boiling water.
Bake in 2 greased 9-inch pans or 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
See fudge recipe for frosting.

title: easy orzo
directions: Brown bacon until crisp; drain.
Add onion and mushrooms; cook until tender.
Add chicken broth and water; bring to a boil.
Stir in orzo and parsley; return to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until orzo is tender.

title: charlie pepper steak
directions: Cut meat in 1-inch wide strips.
Saute meat in butter and oil quickly.
Take out; salt and pepper lightly.
Saute mushrooms and add to meat.
Saute onions and peppers 2 minutes.
Add to meat. Add tomatoes, vinegar, soy sauce and tomato paste to pan and bring to a boil.
Pour over meat.
Toss lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grilled salmon
directions: Combine garlic, dill, olive oil, lemon juice and salt.
Rub over salmon.
Let rest at room temperature for 30 minutes. Grill for 7 to 10 minutes per side or bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with roasted red potatoes with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine and bring to a boil.
Let cool and pour over cucumbers and onions.
Put in freezer.
