Could keep in refrigerator and use. Both ways are very good.

title: jumbo raisin-nut cookies
directions: Boil raisins with water 5 minutes. Drain; measure 1/2 cup of the liquid. Add water if needed to make 1/2 cup. Cool; stir in soda. Cream shortening, sugar and spices. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla and raisin liquid. Sift flour with salt and baking powder and stir into wet mixture. Add raisins and walnuts. Chill dough until stiff. May be kept overnight in refrigerator. Drop by fat teaspoonful about 1-inch apart on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Remove to rack to cool.

title: braised chicken thighs
directions: Combine onions, carrots, celery, garlic and butter in a large Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes.
Add lemon peel and remove from heat.

title: shrimp with scrambled eggs
directions: White Sauce:
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Sprinkle in flour; mix rapidly.
Cook 1 minute. Pour in hot milk and nutmeg.
Cook sauce for 8 minutes over very low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: crushed punch
directions: Mix the orange juice and limeade according to directions on can.
Mix all ingredients.
Freeze in plastic ice cream containers for 48 hours.
Put in punch bowl and pour Shasta strawberry soda over it.

title: burritos
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain off fat thoroughly.
Heat refried beans; simmer 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients and heat through.

title: 5 minute mousse
directions: Beat 1 package Jell-O chocolate flavor fat-free sugar-free instant pudding with wire whisk into 1 1/2 cups cold milk for 1 minute. Stir in 2 cups thawed Cool Whip Lite whipped topping. Spoon into 6 dessert dishes. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Garnish as desired.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Put cabbage in casserole dish.
Mix soup and cream cheese. Pour mixture over cabbage.
Sprinkle on cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all beans well.
Rinse and drain well again.
Add chopped onion, green pepper, and salt and pepper.
Mix sugar, vinegar and oil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over all the beans, pepper and onions.
Stir to mix well. Refrigerate overnight.
Stir before serving.

title: crab muffins
directions: Melt butter and margarine; stir in cheese until melted and add other ingredients, making crabmeat the last.
Toss until heated through.
Serve over heated English muffins.
May bake muffins with crabmeat for a crispier taste!

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add rice, butter and raisins.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover pan and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add sugar; stir well.
Serve hot with milk.

title: filet lyonnaise
directions: Trim fat from tenderloin.
To make a double butterfly cut: Make a lengthwise cut down center of meat, cutting to within 1/2-inch of other side.

With meat cut side up, make 2 more lengthwise cuts, one on either side of the first cut, cutting through thickest portions of meat to within 1/2-inch of other side. Pound slightly with meat mallet to flatten to a 10 x 8-inch rectangle.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples	in greased square pan 8 x 8 x 2-inches. Mix remaining
ingredients
and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with milk or ice cream.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Heat butter, marshmallows, dry milk and milk in saucepan over low heat until smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add dry cereal and coconut.
Stir.
Put into buttered or greased pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Spread evenly.
Cool.
Cut into squares. Makes 36 squares.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With a sharp knife, make a pocket in each chop.
Cook onion in butter until done.
Add all other ingredients to onion and mix well.
Stuff chops with rice mixture, salt and pepper to taste and place chops in a roasting pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and continue to bake 15 minutes more.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Wash and cook rice.
Cool, not too wet.
Heat oil in frypan or wok.
Fry rice with medium heat for short time; keep stirring. Add soy sauce and salt.
Stir.
Add ham and onion and stir for 5 minutes.
Remove to platter.
Place chopped egg on top.
Serves 3.

title: garlic croutons
directions: Cut the bread into 1/2-inch cubes.
Mince the garlic.
Saute the garlic in the oleo.
Add the cubed bread, stirring and tossing until bread is a golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and store in the refrigerator in a jar.

title: cornmeal mush
directions: Heat 5 cups water and the salt to boiling.
Mix cornmeal, flour and brown sugar with 2 cups cold water.
Add mixture slowly to boiling water, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat about 30 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil; boil 2 minutes.
Add oatmeal, nuts and vanilla.
Drop on wax paper.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sour cream with baking soda.
Set aside.
Put butter into a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla and continue beating until well mixed.
Add flour and bananas to the batter, using electric mixer set at low speed.
Add sour cream and mix it with rubber spatula.
Put into greased and floured loaf pan.
(Pam is good to use.)
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Use loaf pan.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Coat with butter, Parmesan cheese and egg mixture.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 pie plates. Spread Ricotta cheese over spaghetti.
Layer top with meat sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.

title: rice casserole
directions: Slightly brown rice in margarine.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir after 1/2 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vanilla wafer cake(torta di vanilla)
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Cream
butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1
at
a time, alternating with milk and crushed wafers until
all ingredients
are
used.
Fold in nuts and coconut. Bake
in greased
and
floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
This cake is very moist (almost wet) and rich.
Serve with a little whipped cream, if desired.

title: mexican pizza
directions: In a small bowl, combine warm water and sugar; add yeast.
Set aside.
In large bowl, place flour, salt and oil.
Wait until yeast mixture has risen (thick and frothy).
Add yeast mixture to flour mixture and knead.
Add a small amount of extra flour, if needed.
The goal is to have a well-mixed dry dough.

title: sara's cheese biscuit
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In a mixing bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Using a pastry cutter, cut the shortening into the dry ingredients until the mixture has the texture of coarse meal. Slowly add the milk and cheese, mixing to form a smooth dough. Turn out onto a floured board and knead lightly. Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with a floured biscuit cutter. Place on an ungreased baking sheet 2-inches apart and bake 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 1 dozen.

title: italian salad
directions: Mix cooked macaroni, peppers, onions, cheese and pepperoni. Set aside.
Mix together oil, vinegar, sugar, oregano, salt and pepper.
Pour over macaroni mixture.
Stir well and marinate overnight.
Then add tomatoes.
Serve.

title: elephant stew
directions: Find a big pan.
Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
This takes about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover and cook over hot fire, about 465°.
Serves approximately 3,800 people.

title: mama cilla's pickles
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers that have been packed in jars.
Seal.
To make dill pickles, pack in the jar with cucumbers, two or three cloves of garlic, dill weed and/or slices of onion.
These pickles are good in about a week or 10 days.

title: mom's egg surprise
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon and onion until bacon is crisp. Drain all but 1/2 cup of the drippings.
Add hash browns to skillet; mix well.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, turning when browned.
Make 10-inch well.
Sprinkle with cheese if desired. Cover and cook over low heat for about 10 minutes or until eggs are set.
Garnish with parsley; serve immediately.
Yields 10 servings.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add boiling water to make a paste.
Add egg.
Drop by tablespoon in hot grease.
Fry until golden brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and put in casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: coconut macaroon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer, except 1/2 cup coconut. Sprinkle the 1/2 cup coconut on top of pie.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: rice pilaf with peas
directions: Brown bacon in large frypan; drain and saute onion, garlic and mushrooms in same pan.
Drain and pour off grease.
In same pan, heat 2 cups water and 2 cubes bouillon.
Add rice and peas; cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes, until rice is tender.
Add drained onion, garlic, mushrooms and crumbled bacon.
Serve.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Stir well.
Gradually add vinegar and soy sauce, stirring until cornstarch mixture is dissolved.
Stir in pineapple, green pepper, onion, mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Set aside.

title: crisp cookies
directions: Flour enough to make a soft dough just stiff enough to roll out thin. Try a pint, working it in gradually. Bake in a quick oven.
If you will press a raisin, cherry and half a pecan or anything of the kind on the top of each cake before baking it adds to the appearance of the cakes.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Knead dough until it forms a soft ball.
Then make into small balls and roll out with a rolling pin.
Cover dough while making tortillas.
Makes about 8 to 10 tortillas.

title: baked chicken
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Add either the chicken or pork loin pieces.
Add Swiss cheese to meat.
Place one layer of Pepperidge Farm dressing over meat.
Cover entire dish with 1 can cream of chicken soup to which you have added 1/2 cup milk.
This is excellent for a large meal.
Very easy to prepare and eliminates a lot of work.
I like this particular dressing the herbs and spices are already in the baked cubes.
Bake at 350°.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions and then drain. Meanwhile, in a heavy saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Gradually stir in cheese and then cream until well blended. Continue heating sauce and stirring constantly, just to boiling point.
Remove from heat and stir in parsley.
Serve over fettuccine.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into a jelly-roll pan. Let cool and ice.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Thaw potatoes 1 hour.
Mix all ingredients together, except potato chips.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased Pyrex baking dish. Put 2 cups of crushed potato chips on top.
Bake for 1 hour in a 375° oven.
Cover with foil (may remove foil before time is up to allow to brown).

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Mix together orange juice and cornstarch.
Add this and the sugar, cinnamon, chicken broth and soy sauce to the onion and peppers in the frypan.
Add the can of pineapple with juice to the pan and cook until it thickens.
Stir in the pea pods and chicken. Serve on patty shells or rice.

title: philly balls(servings:  24)
directions: Gradually mix powdered sugar into cream cheese, vanilla and salt.
This may take a while; everyone can take turns at it. After it is completely mixed, roll into 1-inch balls and roll into shredded coconut.
At Christmas, coconut may be separated and dyed green and red first.

title: mystery cake
directions: Beat eggs; add drained fruit cocktail.
Sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add to egg mixture and mix well.
Spread mixture in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Over this, sprinkle brown sugar and pecans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with Cool Whip and cherries.

title: pizza dough
directions: Beat flour, milk, vegetable oil, baking powder and salt in a bowl until the dough leaves side.
Turn onto a lightly floured surface; gather into a ball.
Knead 10 times. Cover with a bowl. Let stand 15 minutes. Spread onto pan (greased).
Add favorite toppings.

title: homemade apple butter(make in a slow cooker)
directions: In a kettle or Dutch oven, combine apples, cider or juice and vinegar.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: sausage-mushroom stuffing
directions: Cook sausage in hot skillet until well browned.
Remove sausage from pan.
Measure the rendered fat and if sausage has not produced 1/2 cup, add butter to make up difference.
Return fat to pan.
Saute mushrooms, celery and onion for 5 minutes.
Add rest and moisten with broth.
Refrigerate, covered, until ready to use.

title: parmesan zucchini strips
directions: In a bowl, combine the bread crumbs and cheese topping.
Dip zucchini in egg substitute, then crumb mixture.
Place on a baking sheet coated with non stick cooking spray.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown and tender.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first five ingredients.
Spread mayonnaise on top.
Top with cheese and crumbled bacon.
Best if done the night before.

title: lemon filling
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; bring to boiling.
Stir constantly.
Boil 2 minutes.
Stir some mixture into egg; return egg to hot mixture.
Cook 3 minutes.
Stir in rind, butter and juice.
Cool.
Fills 2 layers.

title: wet chicken burritos
directions: Fry onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon oil until tender.
Remove approximately 1/4 of onion mixture and place in another saucepan. Add chicken.
Cover and keep warm.

title: smokie link
directions: Simmer hot dog links with barbecue sauce.
Serve with decorative toothpicks.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Place pork ribs in Dutch oven; add water.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain.
tags: rack fresh pork loin back ribs

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Pour hamburger over macaroni.
Add ketchup, sugar, and salt and pepper, to taste.
Mix together and serve.

title: bread crumb dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate 1/2 hour (easier to handle).
Make into small balls and refrigerate before using.
Can also freeze them.
Excellent in chicken broth.

title: mississippi cornbread
directions: Beat egg in bowl. Add milk. Add sugar, flour and cornmeal. Melt butter in iron skillet. Add to mixture. Stir a little until mixed. Pour into iron skillet. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: no peek stew
directions: Put meat in 4-quart roaster or casserole.
Add vegetables. Blend juice, sugar, salt, tapioca and spices.
Pour over and cover. Cook in oven at 250° to 300° for 4 to 4 1/2 hours.
I found that it cooks best at 250°.
Delicious; tastes every better the next day. You will enjoy this!
Serve with a good "crusty" bread and applesauce.
Remember, don't peek.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add garlic, basil, salt, pepper, tomato paste, tomatoes and oregano.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Mix Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, eggs and parsley.

title: crumble bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, then the rest of the ingredients. Put in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle with 1/2 package of little marshmallows on top.
Bake 3 minutes more, cool real good.

title: grandma fern's calif. tacos
directions: Brown hamburger in a large saucepan on medium heat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain.
Add black olives.
Cut or shred cheese and melt in hamburger mixture.
Reduce to low heat.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash and mash.	Add other ingredients.	Sprinkle top with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican sugar cookies
directions: Beat butter at high speed until light and fluffy.
At low speed beat in sugar, flour, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, vanilla and salt until just combined.
Dough will be stiff.
Shape into a ball. Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Roll dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until cookies are golden.
Combine granulated sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Roll hot cookies in mixture.
Place on wire rack to cool.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: fruit delight
directions: Mix cottage cheese and well drained fruit.
Sprinkle with dry jello; mix well.
Fold in whipped topping; pour in 1-quart loaf dish.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Serve as dessert with whipped topping and cherry or as salad on lettuce with mayonnaise.

title: easy supper for one
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Cook chicken until done.
Pour in undiluted soup.
Season with salt and pepper.
Heat until soup is warm.
Serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding dressing and chips just before serving.
Makes a large bowl.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together. Store in airtight container. Use 3 to 4 teaspoons per cup.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats, oleo and boiling water and let stand for 20 minutes. Add sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, salt and soda and add.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: Melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion and saute until tender.
Add the potatoes, parsley and chicken broth.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Form
into
small
balls.
Cook 1 1/2 inches apart for 8 to
minutes at 350° until brown. Can be frozen in plastic bags and
cooked at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until brown.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add all the ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until firm.

title: dressing
directions: Saute sausage.
Add butter, onion, celery and apple.
Add 1/2 of bread crumbs with the seasonings.
Mix well.
Add rest of crumbs, raisins and pecans.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add flour, salt, vanilla and milk alternately.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
Cool on rack 30 minutes and remove from pan.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine and mix all ingredients (except rice).
Add mixture to rice; bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes until light golden brown.

title: crock-pot cubed steak and gravy
directions: Coat steak in flour, salt and pepper mixture. Fry in large skillet in hot oil until done. Drain steak on paper towel and cut steak into bite-size pieces. Place in crock-pot. Drain oil in pan you cooked steak in and mix the gravy mix following directions on packet, then add mushroom soup and 2 cans of water. Mix well and pour over the steak. Let simmer for 2 hours on low.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Cut up artichokes and mix with mayonnaise and cheese.
Heat in a 300° oven until warm.

title: creamy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions. Drain broccoli. Melt butter, flour, salt, milk and cheese in saucepan. Stir constantly until blended. Put broccoli in 2-quart casserole dish. Add onions. Pour sauce over vegetables. Sprinkle grated Longhorn cheese over top. Cover casserole with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: grape salad
directions: Melt Jell-O in hot water. Add sugar, pineapple and pie filling. Chill until firm or overnight.

title: barbecued beef loaves
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into 8 loaves; place in greased shallow pan.
Pour your favorite barbecue sauce (bottled kind is good) over loaves and bake.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: fudgy banana brownie cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 12 cup fluted tube pan with vegetable cooking spray.
In blender, puree bananas (to yield 1 1/2 cups.)
In medium bowl, stir together bananas, corn syrup, buttermilk, oil and vanilla.
In large mixer bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add banana mixture to flour mixture; beat until well blended.
In small mixer bowl, beat egg whites until stiff; fold small amount into batter. Fold in remaining egg whites.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; invert cake onto wire rack. Cool completely.
Place on serving plate.
Pour banana fudge topping over cake.
Makes 16 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Add chicken broth and chopped broccoli.
Simmer until tender.
Add enough flour to mixture to thicken.
Add milk and cheese (desired choice).
Simmer until cheese is melted and flavor to taste.

title: beer-glazed ham(a christmas tradition)
directions: Heat ham according to package directions.
Meanwhile, to prepare glaze, combine brown sugar, honey, beer and mustard. Score ham and stud with cloves.
Spoon glaze over ham the last 30 minutes of baking.
Serves 14.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add marshmallows, crumbled cheese and 2 cups of boiling water.
Stir until cheese and marshmallows are melted.
Fold in carrots, nuts and pineapple. Chill until firm.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Grind orange, lemon and cranberries. Fix jello according to package directions. When jelled, combine all ingredients.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Place in casserole with peas. Pour soup over this and top with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients, except brown sugar and nuts, in a large mixing bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched and pulls away from sides of pan. (Do not underbake.)
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Spoon on hot Butter Glaze.

title: marion's pork chops
directions: Trim off fat from chops.
Heat fat in skillet and brown slightly.
Put chops in baking pan.
Top with onion rings.

title: tv party mix
directions: Mix in large pan.
Mix oil and seasoning in can or bottle and shake well.
Pour over mixture.
Bake in 250° oven for 2 hours, stirring every 15 to 20 minutes with wooden spoon or pancake turner.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Put meat in a large, heavy pot.
Season with salt and pepper. Add onions and cover with water.
Cook until meat falls from bones (several hours).
Remove from fire and allow to cool.
Remove meat from bones; tear into small shreds and return to stock.
Add tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, catsup, Tabasco, bay leaves, chili sauce, mustard and butter.
Cook for 1 hour, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly until thick.

title: granny's breaded tomatoes
directions: Use
fresh or canned
tomatoes;
heat
until
ready
to boil. Use tomatoes and juice.
Saute onion in butter.
Add to tomatoes with salt and sugar to taste.
Thicken enough to look like gravy. (Make thickening with
flour and water.) Cut 4 to 6 slices of white bread
into
small
squares.	Stir
to cover with melted butter.
Toast
in	oven until golden brown, stirring
often. Pour tomato
mixture
over	toasted
bread.
Mix slightly.	Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions until tender; drain and cool.
Combine with remaining ingredients in a salad bowl and mix gently.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Makes 14 to 16 servings.

title: spinach cornbread casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pickled eggs or sausage
directions: Bring to boil. Pour over eggs or sausage. Set for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and sugar in large bowl until smooth. Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl; add pudding and blend well for 2 minutes (will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin and spices.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: sunshine fluff salad
directions: Combine the undrained pineapple with the gelatin.
Heat until the gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat and add Mandarin oranges and buttermilk.
Refrigerate until cool. Stir in Cool Whip and chill.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: sweet and sour beef
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet; brown beef on all sides. Add salt, tomatoes, brown sugar, vinegar, onion and bay leaf. Cover skillet; lower heat.
Let simmer about 2 hours until beef is tender. Add pepper strips to beef; cook about 10 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add cheese.
Line large dish with 1/2 chips.
Put 1/2 of meat on this.
Add 1/2 of grated cheese.
Add beans, juice and all.
Then add rest of Doritos and rest of meat. Mix Ro-Tel tomatoes and cream of chicken soup together; pour over casserole.
Top with remaining cheese and bake until hot at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: quick breakfast rolls
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths.
Put into plastic bag with sugar and cinnamon.
Layer biscuits into greased tube pan.
Sprinkle chopped nuts between layers.
Melt brown sugar and butter and beat for one minute.
Pour over biscuits and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serve warm.

title: mexi lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna in boiling water with 1 tablespoon olive or cooking oil, until tender (add strips, one at a time, to avoid sticking together).
Drain off hot water and cool with warm water to handle.
Saute onion; set aside.
Brown ground meat and drain off fat.
Add onion, tomato sauce and enchilada sauce.
Cook about 20 minutes.
If sauce is too thick, add a little water (1/2 to 1 cup).

title: saturday chicken
directions: Take the chicken, salt and garlic salt it a bit, then paprika it thoroughly.
Spread it out in one layer in a shallow baking pan.
Mix the soup and the cream in a bowl, then pour it over the chicken.
Bake it, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: gourmet beef tenderloin
directions: To toast almonds:
You can toss them in a dry cast-iron skillet over medium-high heat for a few minutes, until they become fragrant and begin to take on a little color.

title: quick and easy meat loaf
directions: Mix in a deep mixing bowl with hands or a large spoon.
Bake in a deep baking dish at 350°.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All.
Add soup, mayonnaise and onion.
Mix well. Line bottom of casserole dish with crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour in ingredients.
Melt margarine and mix with crushed Ritz crackers. Spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage and egg bake
directions: Brown sausage; drain well. Set aside. Beat eggs. Add milk, spices, cheese and chiles. Mix with bread cubes and sausage. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 10 x 13 baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix butter, 1/2 cup evaporated milk and cake mix together. Spread half of batter in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk and drizzle over the baked batter.
Then sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips over the caramel mixture.
Drop batches of remaining batter on top and then bake 18 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: super party dip
directions: In a medium bowl, blend yogurt and cottage cheese.
Sprinkle in all spices.
Blend well.
Salt to taste.
Cover with plastic wrap. Chill until serving time.
Serve as a dip for vegies.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine ingredients together and pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: cheese lemon chicken
directions: Cut 4 thin slices of lemon; set aside.
Squeeze 1 tablespoon juice from remaining lemon and also set aside.
In a 10-inch skillet, over medium heat, cook chicken in hot oil until browned on both sides, about 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine soup, water, reserved lemon juice and pepper.
Stir into skillet with chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over the chicken; top with lemon slices.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with parsley and serve over orzo or rice.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and jello.
Put in refrigerator until almost jelled.
Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and pecans.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Preheat gas grill to medium.
Prepare sauce.
Combine ketchup, vinegar, horseradish, brown sugar, garlic and thyme.
Mix well. Bring to boil over medium-low heat, stirring frequently until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Stir in pepper.
Remove from heat. Brush chicken with sauce.
Put on grill, cook and enjoy.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cushaw pie
directions: Blend ingredients.
Add nutmeg to flavor.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes or until silver knife inserted into filling comes out clean.

title: 2 minute fudge
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients; cook on high for 2 minutes.
Pour into 8-inch square dish lined with waxed paper. Chill; cut when well set.

title: baked chops and fries
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown pork chops in oil; sprinkle with seasoned salt.
In a bowl, combine the cheese sauce and milk until blended; spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.
Top with cottage fries and half of the onions. Arrange broccoli and pork chops over the top.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining onions.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until the meat is no longer pink and the broccoli is tender.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Fold together all ingredients.
Makes 1 large or 3 small balls.

pan.	Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Do not overbake.
Center will be jiggly but becomes firm upon cooling.
Makes 12 to 18 bars.

title: whisper cake
directions: Spread in layers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: quick and easy pierogi
directions: Place flour in large bowl.
Add water and oil slowly, stirring constantly with a fork, until mixture is crumbly.
Let stand until cool.

title: salisbury steakburgers
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion and pepper.
Shape firmly into 6 patties.
In skillet brown patties. Pour off fat.
Stir in remaining soup and water.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally. Serves 6.

title: southern style pecan fudge(microwave)
directions: In large bowl place butter and milk; microwave 2 minutes. Stir in sugar, cocoa, vanilla and salt until smooth, then stir in nuts.
Spread mix in buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk until it reaches a soft ball stage or a degree below.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter; stir until melted and add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat well.
Pour into pie crust (unbaked) and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in hot oven at 325° until custard is set, about 40 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook the beef and drain.
Add the garlic, salt, tomato sauce and olives.
Put aside.
Mix sour cream, cottage cheese and chilies.
Put aside.

title: cube steak with mushroom soup
directions: Spray casserole dish with Wesson cooking spray.
Place cube steak in dish and sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce.
Top with mushroom soup.
Spread evenly over steak.
Cook at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil the margarine, water and cocoa.
Pour into a large mixing bowl and add the flour, sugar and salt.
Beat these ingredients well, then add the eggs, sour cream and soda.
Beat well and pour into a large greased cooking sheet (11 1/2 x 18-inch).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
While cake bakes, make icing.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix cereals, pretzels and nuts in a large bowl.
Heat oleo, bacon drippings and remaining ingredients until melted.
Pour over cereal mixture. Spread in shallow pan and bake at 250° for about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: corned beef red flannel hash
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, peel and dice.
Dice the meat. Dice the onion.

Carefully take the seeds out of the jalapeno pepper, if you are using it (I like hot food, the spice makes my saliva glands work and since they don't most of the time, I use a lot of hot spices) and chop it fine.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Mix one batch at a time.
Beat eggs until creamy.
Add sugar. Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Melt oleo and milk in pan.
Bring to boil and add to flour mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured round pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
We bake 2 cakes and put Cool Whip and strawberries between layers and on top.

directions: Beat
eggs
until
light.
Add
the
sugar and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Then add the water.
Sift dry ingredients together 3 times and gradually add to the mixture. Lastly,
add
the
vanilla.
Grease

jelly

pan (11 x 15-inch),
place
wax
paper
on the bottom, and grease again, also sprinkle flour over this.
Spread batter on this and bake in a moderately hot oven (stoves vary) for 12 to 15 minutes at 375°. Turn out immediately on a damp towel and remove the wax paper. Spread
with
either jelly or any other filling (lemon is good). Roll like jelly roll.
Makes 12 or 14 servings.

title: no icing chocolate cake
directions: Mix together.
Put in Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Put a cookie sheet under and flip out of pan while still warm.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together to taste and refrigerate for several hours.
Serve with chips.

title: finger pizzas
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix onions, Italian seasoning and cheese.
Cook until cheese has melted and mix well with sausage. Spread mixture onto party bread and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or golden brown.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add yolks, one at a time.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Sift sofa and flour together.
Add flour and sour cream alternately to the butter mix.
Stiffly beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Put into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake shrinks from sides of pan.
Remove from pan as soon as it can be handled comfortably.

title: jones girls' salad dressing
directions: Mix together all ingredients, adding oil last.
Shake well.

title: butterscotch - mocha pound cake
directions: Combine butterscotch morsels, coffee powder and water in top of double boiler.
Place over boiling water and stir until smooth. Set aside.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: halloween cookie pops
directions: In large bowl of an electric mixer, beat shortening, butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar until creamy; beat in eggs and vanilla.
In another bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, salt and pumpkin pie spice; gradually add to butter mixture, blending thoroughly.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.

title: macaroni spaghetti rice casserole
directions: Boil macaroni, spaghetti and rice in water slowly, about 15 minutes.
Drain.
Combine salt, onion, pepper and tomatoes.
Add macaroni, rice and spaghetti.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle top with bread stuffing and cheese.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan. Add flour and milk. Cook until slightly thickened, stirring frequently. Add eggs, green pepper, onion, salt and Worcestershire. Stir in seafood and mayonnaise. Stir well.
Stir in cheese. Pour mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and golden brown on top.

title: holiday slush
directions: Mix water, sugar and fruit juices in a large container.
Add mashed bananas and freeze overnight.
One hour before serving, remove from freezer and add club soda.
Makes a little more than 1 punch bowl.

title: barbecued potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut potatoes crosswise in thin slices. Spray baking pan with cooking spray.
Place potatoes on pan.
In a small bowl, combine rest of the ingredients.
Spread evenly over potatoes.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, until tender.
Makes 4 servings with 160 calories and 4 grams fat.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Cube chicken breasts and place in large soup pan with 1/2 cup butter.
Cook with carrots (sliced thin), and chopped onion.
Add corn (do not drain), mushrooms, chicken broth and cubes.
Simmer 2 hours.
Add roux, 2 cups cream and 2 cups Cheddar cheese.
Do not boil after adding cheese.
Serve with fresh green salad and your favorite bread to make a delicious meal.

title: cheese roll
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Mix together well. Roll out on waxed paper sprinkled with chili powder and garlic salt.
Serve with crackers.
Keep refrigerated.

title: nonalcoholic eggnog(yields 1 gallon)
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in milk, heavy cream, vanilla and rum extract. Add salt to egg whites and beat to soft peaks.
Fold into mixture.

title: protein snacks
directions: Mix all together and roll into 1-inch balls.
Refrigerate. Makes about 8 balls.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Fill a well oiled baking dish with alternate layers of well seasoned cooked tomatoes, butter and bread cubes.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hearty potato-leek soup
directions: In large pot, heat the canola oil.
Add potatoes, leeks, onions and garlic.
Saute vegetables over medium-high heat until they are translucent, about 5 to 6 minutes.
Add the chicken broth to mixture.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes until vegetables are tender. Remove from heat.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine marinade ingredients, whisking together thoroughly in a large bowl. Cut tips from wings and discard. Cut wings at joint. Add wings to marinade.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 to 2 days. Stir a couple of times each day.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Place wings in a single layer on sheet. Cook for at least 1 hour at 350°.

title: island pie
directions: Whip together the cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Mix in pineapple and then peaches.
Fold in whipped topping. Pour into pie shell and garnish with cherries.
Chill until serving time. Serves 8 to 10.

title: deviled clams
directions: Cook bread crumbs in milk.
When thick, add butter, pepper, parsley, onion and clams.
Cook 10 minutes over medium fire. Add hard-boiled eggs.
Fill large clam shells with mixture, topping with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion in skillet.
Drain excess fat. Set aside.
Mix both packages of pizza crust mix together, following directions on package.
Place dough in a large casserole dish.
Pour ground chuck and onion mixture over crust, then pour tomato sauce evenly over ground chuck.
Apply Mozzarella cheese over entire mixture.
Bake at 400° until cheese is slightly browned.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onions and carrots in salt water until tender. Drain.
Add soup, sour cream and pimento. Melt margarine and mix with dressing mix.
Grease casserole dish.
Spread 1/2 of dressing mix on bottom of dish.
Pour in mixture and top with remaining dressing mix.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix all together in heavy saucepan.
Stir and cook until thick.
Serve over hot buttered biscuits.

title: frozen lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press firmly on bottom of an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
In small mixer bowl, beat egg yolks, sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 8 minutes. Cool. Top with whipped topping or cream.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Freeze any leftovers.
(Dessert can be chilled instead of frozen.)

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil.
Dissolve cornstarch in 3/4 cup cold water.
Add to sugar mixture.
Cook 10 minutes over low heat until clear.
Blend in salt, lemon juice and enough red food coloring to produce bright red color.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Mix together and freeze.
Add lemon-lime soda if desired.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add the crackers, chocolate and butterscotch bits, coconut and nuts in layers as listed.
After layering the ingredients, pour the milk over top. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Be careful not to overbake.

title: blt dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill to blend flavors.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: stew beef
directions: Place roast into crock-pot.
Add salt, pepper, onion, corn and green beans.
Add potatoes, if desired.
Do not drain vegetables. Add it to the roast.
Cook on low heat all day and enjoy it for supper.

title: best zucchini bars
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat well.
Gradually add oil.
Beat in flour, salt, soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes, until well mixed.
Fold in zucchini, carrot and oats.
Pour into a 15 x 10-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar icing, if desired.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Blend flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in large mixing bowl. Stir in cereal.
Add buttermilk (or substitute), oil and egg. Blend until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not overmix.
Fill lightly greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Makes 1 dozen.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
If desired, lightly brush melted butter over batter and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar before baking.

title: zucchini "apple" pie
directions: Peel zucchini, cut in quarters lengthwise, remove seeds, slice crosswise, and cook until tender-crisp.
Toss with lemon juice and salt.
Mix in a bowl sugar, cinnamon, cream of tartar, nutmeg and flour.
Add the zucchini and mix well.
It will be runny, but that's okay.
Dump the filling into a 9-inch crust and dot with butter.
Add the top crust and bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
This really tastes like apple pie!

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain well.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Add dressing and toss.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Cook onions and celery in skillet with 1 stick butter over low heat for 1/2 hour.
Add bread and chicken broth.
Add all other ingredients.
Pull chicken off the bones.
Make dressing fairly thin so it will not be dry when done.
Top with butter before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix all very well.
Pour mixture into holes and allow to cool in pan before taking out.

title: turkey rice broccoli casserole
directions: Roast turkey until meat falls off bone.
Remove meat from bone and cut in bite sizes.
Add enough water to broth to make 2 1/4 to 2 1/2 cups.
Add turmeric, onion, celery and broccoli.
Put rice on top of broccoli.
Be sure to push rice just under the broth. Cover and bring to a boil and cook 10 to 15 minutes or until rice is just done.
Add soup. Put in casserole and put grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese melted.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Sprinkle cinnamon/sugar mixture over melted butter.
Sprinkle pecans on top of that.
Place biscuits on butter mixture and bake at 400° until done.
Invert on plate.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Place chilies in bottom of greased casserole dish. Arrange cheese in and around chilies.
Pour beaten eggs over all. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Top with black olives.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour.
Test with a toothpick.

title: pauline's christmas fruit salad
directions: Chill the evaporated milk in an ice tray until frozen around edges.
In a 2-quart bowl, dissolve the Jell-O in the boiling water.
Stir in the cold water. Add the marshmallows, pineapple, chopped nuts and apples to the Jell-O mixture and let stand.
Now whip the milk in a cold bowl until stiff. Fold into Jell-O mixture. Chill well before serving.
(Your favorite flavor of Jell-O makes the color.
I like mixed fruit.)

title: jello delight
directions: Prepare orange jello in the usual manner.
Add drained pineapple and marshmallows before placing in refrigerator to chill and set.
Make sure the jello mixture is put in a bowl large enough to accommodate the second layer.

title: navy beans with savory
directions: Soak the beans overnight in 2 quarts water.
Drain the beans and add fresh water to cover; salt to taste.
Add the onion and savory and bring to a boil.
Lower the flame and simmer gently until tender, about 3 hours.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: cherry pineapple crisp
directions: Combine pineapple, cherry pie filling and cherries.
Place these ingredients in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix on top of this.
Sprinkle pecans on top of the cake mix.
Pour stick of melted margarine or button on top.
Bake at 350°
for about 30 minutes. Until top is browned.

title: creamed ham on toast
directions: In a skillet, saute the ham, green pepper and celery in butter for 4 to 5 minutes. Sprinkle with flour; stir until smooth and bubbly. Add the milk, pepper and celery seed; bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes. Remove from the heat. Add egg and cheese; stir until cheese melts. Serve over toast. Yield: 2 to 3 servings.

title: chicken bake(individual servings)
directions: Season half broiler with salt, pepper and paprika and place, skin side down, on large, lightly oiled square of heavy-duty foil. Dot with butter or margarine and place vegetables in cavity.
Top with bacon.
Add additional seasoning, if desired.
Seal package and place on medium hot coals for about 1 1/2 hours, turning occasionally.
During the last 15 minutes of cooking time, poke several holes in the foil so the chicken can brown.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well; spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish and sprinkle with another 1/2 cup of grated Cheddar. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve immediately, hot.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper. Sprinkle half the mixture on one side of the round steak and pound on.
Repeat for the other side.
Cut meat into pieces.
Melt butter in skillet and brown meat.
Cover tightly and simmer for 1 hour.
Add water, if necessary.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat. Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until tender.

title: knox blox
directions: Mix together unflavored and flavored gelatins in a large bowl. Add boiling water; stir until gelatin dissolves.
Pour into large, shallow 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and chill until firm.
Cut into squares and enjoy.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Put bread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with sausage or ham. In blender, mix eggs, milk, margarine, onion salt, mustard, garlic salt and green pepper (if desired). Pour over bread and meat. Sprinkle cheese over all. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 325° about 50 minutes or until done. You may top with crushed potato chips the last 15 minutes of baking.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Whisk 1/2 cup water, chili sauce, egg, mustard and chili powder in a bowl.
Stir in oats; let stand 5 minutes.
Add turkey, bell peppers, scallions and frozen corn to oat mixture.
Mix lightly.
Shape into loaf; put in loaf pan.
Bake 40 minutes. Spread rest of chili on loaf.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: brown soup stock
directions: Wipe beef and cut lean meat into inch cubes; brown 1/3 in hot frying pan.
Put remaining 2/3 with bone and fat into soup skillet; add water and allow to stand 30 minutes.
Place on back of range; add browned meat and heat gradually to boiling point. Cover and cook slowly for 6 hours.
Add vegetables and seasoning 1 hour before it is finished.
Strain and put away to cool.
Remove all fat; reheat and serve.

title: party potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a saucepan, melt butter.
Add cheese, heat, stirring until cheese is melted.
Add sour cream, green onions, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Scoop potatoes from skins and add to casserole. Toss potatoes in sour cream mixture just to coat potatoes. Sprinkle paprika over all.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: chicken breasts with rice
directions: Sprinkle uncooked rice in buttered baking dish.
Pour can of soup and water over.
Sprinkle onion soup on rice mixture.
Place chicken breasts on top, skin side up.
Sprinkle lightly with salt, pepper and paprika.
Cover with foil.
Bake 2 hours at 325°. Uncover for the last 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot pea soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot except ham.
Add 7 cups water and cover.
Cook on high for 6 hours or low for 12 hours until the peas fall apart.
Add ham last few hours of cooking.

title: glazed pork chops with apples
directions: Heat oil in medium size skillet over medium heat.
Add chops; cook, turning occasionally until cooked through, 8 to 10 minutes. Transfer to warm platter.
Pare, core and cut apples crosswise into rings, about 1/4-inch thick.
Add rings to skillet; cook 2 to 3 minutes or until lightly browned.
Add apple juice concentrate. Bring to boiling.
Stir in mustard, salt and pepper.
Spoon over chops.
Serve with asparagus or sweet potatoes and stuffing.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour into pie shell. Bake 15 minutes. Then lower oven to 350 and bake 30 more minutes.

title: quick pizza
directions: Cut muffins in half.
Spread sauce evenly.
Add toppings as you like.
Microcook until cheese melts.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix as listed.
Use tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, flour, mustard and pineapple juice.
Cook until thick.
Cool; add to salad.
Chill before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Stir soup until smooth.
Add milk and pepper.
In buttered casserole, alternate layers of potatoes, onion, green pepper, sauce and cheese.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle top with paprika. Cover; bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender; blend 3 minutes.
Add 1 cup coconut, if desired.
Pour mixture into a greased 10-inch pie dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and at 350° for 35 minutes more.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Add sugar gradually continuing to cream until light and fluffy.
Add egg and extract and beat. Sift flour, salt and baking powder
together.
Add
in
3 additions. Beat well after each addition.
Chill dough 10 minutes. Pack into cookie press and
press
shapes onto ungreased cookie sheet. Makes
60 to 70 when dial
is
set	between
thin
and medium. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken tortilla pie
directions: Slice 1/2 green pepper into thin strips; set aside for garnish. Coarsely chop for the other half.
Overlap 6 tortillas in circular pattern on bottom of 10-inch quiche dish.
Top with chicken strips, 1/2 cup of the shredded cheese, chopped green peppers and half of the diced tomato.
Beat together soup and salsa in medium-sized bowl until blended.
Slowly stir in milk until smooth.
Lightly beat in eggs.
Measure 1 1/2 cups of egg-milk mixture; reserve. Pour remaining egg-milk mixture over top of chicken.
Arrange remaining tortillas over top.
Pour reserved 1 1/2 cups egg-milk mixture over all.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (375°) for 40 minutes. Lower oven temperature to 350°.
Uncover, bake for 20 minutes or until bubbly hot.
Garnish with remaining tomato and green pepper strips.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix fruit, pour in baking pan, sprinkle dry cake mix over top of fruit.
Melt butter, pour over top of mix.
Sprinkle with nuts. Bake 350° until golden brown or around 30 minutes.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Trim fat from meat and brown in shortening in a Dutch oven. Combine all other ingredients, except cabbage and buns.
Place meat in a roasting pan, pour sauce over it and cover.
Bake at 325° for about 3 hours.
Remove meat from oven and shred with two forks.
Mix with sauce in pan.* When ready to serve, heat meat in sauce and serve on buns with shredded cabbage.

title: sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blot sausage dry with paper towels and combine with cheese, Ranch salad dressing, olives and red pepper. Lightly grease a mini muffin tin and press one won ton wrapper in each cup.
Brush with oil.
Bake 5 minutes until golden.
Remove from tins; place on a baking sheet.
Fill with sausage mixture. Bake 5 minutes, until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until just tender.
Drain and place in a greased casserole dish.
Make a sauce of the butter, flour, salt, pepper and cheese.
Sprinkle almonds over broccoli, then pour over sauce. Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package; drain.
Saute onion in butter.
In a 9 x 13-inch glass dish put a layer of broccoli, a layer of sauteed onion and garlic, layer of sliced cheese rounds and layer of mushroom soup and repeat layers.
Then sprinkle top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: luscious raspberry dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add raspberries and stir until thawed.
Spoon into sherbet glasses.
Chill several hours, until set.
Beat cheese and milk until fluffy; gradually add Marshmallow Whip, beating until blended.
Fold in coconut and almond extract.
Spoon over jello before serving.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Drain off grease.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in casserole dish.
Place thinly sliced potatoes and onion on top of hamburger.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: pickled prunes
directions: Simmer about 1 hour or until prunes are plump.
Place the prunes in a jar and drain the liquid over them to cover, straining out the spices.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cut bacon fine and fry.
Brown onion in fat; stir in flour, then add other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over diced hot potatoes and toss.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, butter, water and vinegar.
Cook on low heat until smooth and thick.
Add beets.
Heat thoroughly and serve at once.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Melt cheese in milk and mustard.
Add raw rice (cooked) and 1/4 pound package chipped beef.
Boil peppers until nearly tender. Stuff with rice mixture.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned on top and heated through, about 30 minutes.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cream margarine and sugar; mix in eggs and pears.
Sift flour and dry ingredients and stir in.
Fold in nuts.
Bake for about 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, soup, water and onion and spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Roll washed chicken breasts in dry soup mix. Place chicken on top of rice mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: all american lemonade
directions: Combine water and sugar in small saucepan over medium heat and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 to 6 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and cool syrup completely.
Combine syrup with lemon juice and zest.
Add 8 cups water.
Garnish and serve over ice.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts lemonade.

title: jello angel food cake
directions: Pinch up angel food cake and place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix jello according to directions on box and let it set up about halfway.
Add Cool Whip to jello.
Beat until mixed well and is smooth.
Add drained crushed pineapple to jello mixture.
Mix well.
Pour over cake pieces.
Top with nuts if desired.
Chill.

title: marinated smokies
directions: Put ingredients into crock-pot on low heat for 1 1/2 hours and serve.

title: giblet gravy
directions: For each cup of gravy, leave 1 tablespoon fat drippings and all crusty brown particles in the roasting pan.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon cornstarch into pan.
Stir over medium heat just until smooth; remove from heat.
Slowly stir in 1 cup Giblet Broth until smooth. Stir in reserved chopped giblets and neck meat.
Stirring, bring to boil over medium heat; boil 1 minute or until thickened.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: reese's
directions: Layer one:
pound cake, brownies, soft chocolate chunk cookies or dessert shells.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange green beans or broccoli in bottom of 2-quart shallow baking dish; set aside.
In small saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour.
Gradually stir in milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add cheese, onion mixture and pepper; heat until cheese melts and soup mix is dissolved.
Pour evenly over vegetables.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar gradually, beating until thick.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Fill container with milk to fill line.
Freeze in 5-quart freezer.

title: banana split cake
directions: Fill 9 x 13-inch pan with graham cracker crust (1 stick oleo) and pat into pan.
Mix sugar, 1 stick oleo, vanilla and egg.
Pour this mixture over crust.
Add drained pineapple, then add bananas (cut lengthwise).
Then add Cool Whip on top, then put cherries on top, cut up finely.
Then top with pecans and chocolate syrup, drizzled on top.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of water with salt. Drain and mash.
Add egg, oleo, cheese, pepper and 1/2 the cracker crumbs.
Mix well and shape into balls.
Roll balls in remaining cracker crumbs.
Fry in deep fat.

title: tomato dumplings
directions: Pour tomatoes in 4 quart pan.
Add onion, garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil, stirring to prevent scorching. Turn heat down and continue to simmer.
Mix bisquick and milk. Drop by teaspoonfuls into simmering tomatoes.
Cook uncovered for ten minutes.
Cover and cook ten more minutes.

title: chicken saute
directions: Cook chic-kette and garlic in margarine over low heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in vegetables.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are heated, stirring occasionally. Add cheese, stir until melted.
Serve over rice.
Top with pecans.

title: jello dessert
directions: Stir water in Jell-O.
Cool to room temperature, about 30 minutes.
Pour milk into a mixing bowl and add pudding.
Blend 1 to 2 minutes into Jell-O.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Pour the boiling water over the jello. Dissolve.
Put in frozen strawberries.
Add pineapple and juice.
Mix together and pour a layer in mold.
Set in refrigerator.
Whip the Dream Whip and spread on top of jello in mold.

title: chicken salad sandwich
directions: After preparing eggs and chicken, mix together and let chill. Serve on crackers or bread.

title: beer waffles
directions: Combine the flour, egg yolks, sugar, butter, salt, vanilla, beer and milk in a bowl and beat until smooth.
Whip the egg whites until stiff and fold into the dough mixture.
Spread a little of the batter on a waffle iron and cook.
Serve with confectioners sugar and whipped cream.

title: brown sugar chews
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine and remove from heat.
Sift flour into melted margarine; add brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Sprinkle nuts on top and press down with a spoon.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Will not look done, but it is.
Makes 35.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion and celery.
Stir in flour. Turn into lightly greased crock-pot.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook on high until cheese is melted, stirring often. Turn to low and cook 2 to 4 hours.

title: melt in your mouth blueberry muffins
directions: Add sour milk to eggs.
Add oil and sugar.
Sift together and add flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add blueberries and vanilla.
Mix and pour into greased muffin tins. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain cauliflower and broccoli well.
Cut into small bite-size pieces.
Mix all together and refrigerate for 1/2 day.

title: vicki mckeever's potato supreme
directions: Grate potatoes coarsely.
Mix with remaining ingredients in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: quick strawberry pie
directions: Bring sugar, water and cornstarch to a boil; cook until mixture thickens.
Add jello; stir in well.
Place strawberries in pie shells.
After mixture has cooled, pour over berries into pie shells.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients; place in a small bowl.
Add onion, buttermilk and water, mixing well.
Add butter and egg. Drop by small teaspoonfuls into preheated deep fat.

title: fanny flagg's fried green tomatoes
directions: Dip slices of tomatoes in batter and fry in oil.

title: baked chili rellenos
directions: Spray oil in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Line bottom of pan with chilies (open and lay flat).
Remove seeds.
Cover with cheese.
Beat eggs for 2 minutes.
Add salt, milk and Bisquick mix to eggs and mix thoroughly.
Pour over peppers and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crunch cookies up until they look like dirt.
Melt stick of margarine and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cookies until a thin crust is formed.
Place in freezer until it hardens.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a medium bowl; set aside. Combine egg and hot sauce.
Stir in buttermilk.
Pour into dry ingredients, stirring just enough to mix.
Stir in onion and corn (do not over mix batter).
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Fry until brown.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix well. Add buttermilk and egg; stir. Add melted shortening; mix and turn into greased iron skillet. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
Melt 1 stick margarine in large casserole dish; add sauteed onion and pepper and remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake at 450° for 1 hour (425° if using a glass dish).

title: sweet and sour sauce over smoked sausage
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Pour over smoked sausage.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Add to corn bread mix the sugar, onion, cheese, chilies and creamed corn.
Mix the salad oil, eggs and milk together; add to dry ingredients.
Stir well and pour into greased skillet.
Bake until lightly brown.
Cool before cutting.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni as package label directs; drain.
Melt butter or margarine in medium saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk. Bring to boiling, stirring.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 minute. Remove from heat.

title: southwest stir-fry
directions: For marinade, in a medium mixing bowl combine fajita mix, water and oil.
Rinse chicken and add to marinade.
Stir to coat.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel boiled potatoes.
Cut in cubes.
Chop up eggs.
Put remaining ingredients in bowl and beat until smooth.
Pour over mixture.
Chill 4 hours in refrigerator or overnight.

title: chicken bake
directions: Place in baking dish in this order.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: healthy strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Mix the first four ingredients together, place equally between the two pie crusts and freeze for four hours.
If desired, garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan, cut biscuits in fourths and layer in pan, alternating with mixture of brown sugar, oleo and cinnamon.
Bake approximately for 1 hour at 325°.

title: imperial cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla and vinegar and stir.
Add baking soda and flour; mix well.
Drop on cookie sheet and press down with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake
at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(Check first batch for timing.)

title: german raw apple cake
directions: Mix together. DO NOT use mixer. Pour into a greased pan. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°. Frost when cool.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix together flour, shortening, sugar and salt.
In separate bowl, mix together vinegar, egg and water.
Combine all ingredients and chill at least 15 minutes.
Yield:
3 (9-inch) pie crusts.
Can be refrigerated 3 days or frozen if desired.

title: pancit(rice noodles)
directions: Brown garlic, onion, carrots and celery in 1 tablespoon hot grease.
Add meat and dissolve in (1 cup) hot water the bouillon cube.
Add cabbage and noodles and cover with water.
Steam until noodles are limp and soft.

title: ham and bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Place in a large pot with ham bone and water. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beans are tender, about 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Remove bone and meat.
When cooled, cut meat from bone and return to pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir.

title: salmon bake
directions: Mix all together; put in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: swedish julekaker
directions: Mash yeast with 1 teaspoon sugar and stir in about 3 tablespoons of lukewarm milk.
Stir in 1 or 2 tablespoons of flour to a cake batter consistency.
Let stand 10 minutes in a warm, but not hot, place.
Mix the rest of the flour with cardamon and sugar.
Melt half of the butter in the milk and add sugar mixture; stir well.

title: coludia
directions: Mix eggs, water, sugar and cinnamon. Brush Coludia before baking.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Combine scalded milk, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Soften yeast in lukewarm water and combine with cooled milk mixture.
Add about half the flour; beat well.
Add enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Mix thoroughly.
Knead until smooth and satiny.
Brush surface lightly with melted shortening, cover and let rise in a warm place, about 2 hours or until double in bulk.
Turn out on board and roll dough 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in rounds with biscuit cutter.
Butter lightly with melted butter.
Make a crease across the center of each round, using the dull edge of a knife; fold over.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: kracker kandy
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil and cover with saltine crackers.
Melt butter and margarine and add brown sugar.
Bring to a rolling boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers spreading evenly. Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Pour bag mini chocolate chips on top and spread evenly as they melt.
Sprinkle with pecan chips. Refrigerate.
When cooled, peel foil off back of candy and break into bite size pieces.
Enjoy!

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in small balls.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed pizza
directions: Place one pizza on greased baking sheet.
Cut sausage into thin slices.
Arrange sausage and olives on top.
Sprinkle with half the cheese.
Top with second pizza, upside-down.
Cover with foil.

title: bible cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat together.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to egg mixture.
Add milk and beat well.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Icing is optional (caramel is good).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain and pour sauce over.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° until it bubbles.

title: beef and macaroni
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, macaroni, onion and green pepper. Add salad dressing. Heat. Top with cheese.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Stir together graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter. Press mixture evenly in bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Remove to wire rack and cool completely. Beat cream cheese and cream of coconut at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth. Add pudding mix, beating until blended. Stir in coconut. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread cream cheese mixture evenly into prepared crust. Cover and chill 2 hours or until set. Beat whipping cream with electric mixer until soft peaks form and spread evenly over top of pie. Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cheese and spread over pineapple in a Pyrex dish. Top with crushed Ritz crackers. Pour melted margarine over the top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: men's delight
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually beat 1 cup sugar into eggs.
Add baking powder. Stir vanilla, nuts and crackers into mixture.
Spread into greased pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate, covered, for 24 hours.
Cut in wedges.
Combine whipped cream and remaining sugar.
Fold in strawberries.
Top pie and serve.

title: pot pie dough
directions: Mix the eggs and milk; add to the flour to form a ball.
Roll out and cut into strips, squares, or any desired shapes.
Drop into boiling beef or chicken broth (stock) and cook until dough is done.
(Potatoes and parsley may be added to broth before pot pie dough.)

title: penuche(microwave)
directions: Use a 2-quart Pyrex bowl and microwave the oleo until melted (1 minute).
Stir in sugar until dissolved.
Stir in milk and return to microwave for 11 minutes on High.
Stop every 2 minutes and stir.
After 11 minutes, remove and stir in vanilla and beat with a wooden spoon for 3 minutes.
Fold in nuts and put in a buttered square pan.
Cool for 20 minutes and then put in refrigerator for 20 minutes.
Take out and cut into squares.

title: crisp butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat and add the egg; beat some more. Fold in flour, soda and salt.
Knead well adding more flour as needed to make a stiff dough.
Shape into rolls and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Slice thin and bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 8 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: quick no-cook fondant
directions: Combine frosting mix and margarine in food processor or bowl. Work with steel blade or spoon until mixture is well blended.
Add very small amounts of water if needed.
Mixture will be very stiff at first; work and knead until mixture is well blended and smooth. Use as directed in recipe.
Exchange full recipe:
7 bread and 16 fat.
Calories full recipe:
Yield:
1 cup.

title: jumbles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, beat butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg.
Combine flour and baking soda; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in M&M's baking bits, raisins and nuts.

title: banana bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 1 cup flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add mashed bananas, shortening or butter and milk.
Beat with electric blender on low speed until blended, then on high speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and remaining flour.
Beat until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan. Bake in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Makes one loaf; 16 servings.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Mix oleo, flour, pepper and salt.
Add cheese, then Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Then mash with fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: roast beef
directions: Liberally sprinkle roast with Worcestershire sauce.
Spread mushroom soup completely over roast.
Sprinkle on dry soup mix. Wrap completely in foil.
Roast at 325° for 4 to 5 hours.

title: apple pie
directions: Put apples in crust.
Melt sugar, margarine and water together.
Pour over apples in crust.
Slice top crust and put on pie.
Cook at 375° until done.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening in flour, then add remaining ingredients. Roll out and put in pan.
Yields 2 pie crusts (top and bottom).

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain green beans and peas in colander.

title: ginger apricot muffins(this is a low-cholesterol recipe)
directions: Sift together the flours, salt, baking soda and baking powder. Combine the ginger, egg whites, canola oil, buttermilk, vanilla, brown sugar, poppy seed and cinnamon.
Stir in the flour mix and the diced apricots until well blended. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes in muffin tins.
Batter may be made in advance and refrigerated.
Makes 2 dozen muffins.

title: chocolate gooey bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat margarine in jelly roll pan in oven until melted. Sprinkle and pat cake mix (dry) over margarine. Sprinkle with marshmallows, chocolate chips and Cheerios.
Drizzle milk over top. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frangos
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler and allow to cool.
In a bowl, heat margarine or butter and powdered sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla and cooled chocolate chips.
Add flavoring.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into oblong glass dish. Refrigerate.

title: fruit pot pie
directions: Mix together and pour into cake pan.

title: italian chicken
directions: Heat 1/2 cup olive oil.
Add 1/2 pound deboned chicken breasts, cut in strips, salted, and peppered and lightly dusted in flour. Brown slightly.
Then add the other ingredients one at a time in order.
Toss over low heat for a few minutes and serve topped with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: oriental stir-fry
directions: Add first 7 ingredients to large skillet.
Cook until carrots are tender.
Add rice, salt, pepper, sugar, soy sauce and oil; mix well (about 5 minutes); then add green onions.
Ready to serve.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Combine this and let stand until bubbly.

title: miss lucy's buttermilk pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes. Easy and good.
Freezes well.

title: good meat loaf recipe
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all of the ingredients.
In a large, greased baking pan, shape mixture into a loaf.
Bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: almond poppy bread
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Makes 2 loaves (well-greased pan).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in 3 or 4-quart saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat; allow to cool, then add sugar, molasses, egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir together flour, soda, spices and salt; add to first mixture.
Mix well and chill thoroughly.
Form in 1-inch balls; roll in granulated sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: veal sebastiani
directions: Brown veal in olive oil and butter.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to both sides.
Turn frequently until brown.
Add garlic, parsley, mushrooms, sage and heated wine.
Cover.
Simmer for 30 minutes, until gravy is golden and slightly thickened.

title: chicken supreme casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup with mushrooms

title: cranberry mold
directions: Put cold water into blender.
Add gelatins and 1 cup boiling water.
Cover and process until dissolved.
Remove feeder cap; add orange.
Process until orange is finely ground.
Add cranberries and process until blended.
Place in 1 quart mold.
Chill.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco, egg, pumpkin and vanilla.
Mix in a separate bowl the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Combine dry ingredients with the creamed mixture.
You may add 1/2 cup raisins and/or 1/2 cup chopped walnuts.
After baking last sheet of cookies, make frosting.

title: chocolate fudge(makes approximately 25 pieces)
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Add milk, stirring occasionally.
Let the ingredients cook for approximately 10 to 15 minutes or until thickens.
Then add margarine, salt and vanilla.
Cook another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: "never peek" stew(serves 6)
directions: Put all ingredients in Dutch oven and toss around well. Bake 4 1/2 to 5 hours at 250° with tight cover. Never peek. Do not brown meat.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda. Combine butter, the sugars, vanilla and pudding mix in large mixing bowl. Beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chocolate chips. (Batter will be stiff.) Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tuna straw casserole
directions: Mix together, reserving 1 cup
shoestring potatoes for the top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: deviled crab casserole
directions: Chop onion and bell pepper and saute in 1/2 stick butter until tender.
Beat eggs and add them to all other ingredients including sauteed onions and pepper.
Pour mixture into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and with 1/4 stick butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: impossible tuna pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate. Mix tuna, cheeses, onions and pimiento in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes. Serve with sliced tomatoes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix and bake 1/2 hour at 350 degrees in a lightly greased pie pan.
This is a delicious dish for a brunch or a light dinner!

title: tenderized cube steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat steak with flour; dip in egg, then back in flour.
Brown on both sides over medium heat. Remove from skillet.
Add seasoned flour; stir.
Add milk and cook until thickened.
Serve on steak.
Also can be put on rice or creamed potatoes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Jus mix all together and chill.
Stir before serving.
Best if chilled at least 4 hours.

title: pork and bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well; refrigerate at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: yum-a-setla
directions: Brown meat with salt, pepper, sugar and onion.
Add tomato soup.
Cook egg noodles and drain. Add cream of chicken soup. Layer meat mixture and noodle mixture in casserole dish with cheese between layers.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: uncooked chocolate cookies
directions: Melt and bring to a boil the sugar, milk, cocoa, salt and butter.
Remove from heat and stir in the rolled oats, coconut, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper and let cool.
