title: cheese straws
directions: Combine the dry ingredients before adding the water.
Add the water and blend with a pastry cutter.
I grate the cheese using a Mouli (rotary) grater to make hair-like threads.
Combine the cheese and dough with your fingers.

title: cheese grits
directions: Add grits and salt to boiling water.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until thick.
Add eggs and milk; mix.
Add cheese and margarine. Cook until melted.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: ground beef and green bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbled; drain. Alternate layers of ground beef, potatoes, green beans, and onions in baking dish until all ingredients are used, season with salt and pepper to taste. Spoon tomato soup over top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Serves 4.

title: bread pudding
directions: Measure bread in a cup, pressing firmly.
Melt margarine in 1-quart baking dish; add bread squares.
Toss until coated.
Beat eggs until blended; stir in sugar, salt, nutmeg, vanilla and milk. Slowly pour over bread.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Set dish in pan of hot water.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes or until firm. Remove from hot water; cool on rack.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased pan for one hour.

title: tangy seafood salad
directions: Cook pasta shells according to package directions.
Drain well.
Add crab, onions, peas and tomatoes.
Blend together mayonnaise, sour cream, mustard, vinegar and pepper.
Carefully blend dressing ingredients into pasta mixture.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all ingredients on highest speed of a blender for 50 seconds.
Serve in long stemmed glasses.
Refreshing on a warm day!

title: mango cheesecake
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.
Add flour.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.
Cool completely, about 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Mix corn syrup and peanut butter. Add dry milk and sugar. Roll into balls and chill. Serve.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Mix ingredients and store in a jar.
Use 3 tablespoons to 1 cup boiling water when ready to serve.

title: mediterranean bean salad(ethnic)
directions: Chop up green pepper, tomato, onion and parsley.
Crumble 1/2 to 1 whole package Feta cheese.
Mix with salad dressing and serve.

title: chicken wings
directions: Heat, don't boil.
Add raw chicken wings; stir and coat.
Let boil for 20 minutes, covered.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours uncovered on stove or in oven at 350° at least 1 hour.

title: layered mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onions.
Line 9 x 13 casserole dish with half of flour tortillas.
Layer meat and onion mixture on top of tortillas.
Layer refried beans, then layer slices of velveeta cheese. Put another layer of tortillas.
Spread cream of celery soup on top of tortillas.
Top with the Rotel Tomatoes. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up cabbage and boil until tender.
Drain cabbage and add Cheez Whiz and cream of chicken.
Pour into casserole dish and cover with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pecan rolls in bundt pan
directions: Put pecans in bottom of greased 10-inch Bundt pan. Arrange frozen rolls on top of pecans. Sprinkle with dry pudding mix. Melt butter with brown sugar and white sugar. Pour melted ingredients over top of rolls. Leave on counter, covered with a dish towel, overnight. Bake at 350° for 25-35 minutes. Invert onto a large plate or pan - will have lots of syrup.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together.
Butter a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream pie
directions: Beat eggs real good; add flour and a little milk.
Mix well; add rest of ingredients.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 pat of butter.
Pour in pie shell (cooked).

title: no bake chocolate fudge tart
directions: In microwave-safe bowl, combine half & half and 2 tablespoons sugar. Heat mixture in microwave on high 1-1/2 minutes. Add chocolates and vanilla, stirring until chocolate is melted. Pour mixture into pie crust. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Before serving, beat heavy cream until soft peaks form. Spread over chocolate filling.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, celery, mayonnaise, onions and cheese.
Put in large, greased casserole dish.
Put cracker crumbs in melted margarine.
Brown.
Put crumbs on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar. On a cookie sheet, roll out cookie dough so that it covers the entire sheet. Cook cookie dough as directed. Let cool. Spread the cream cheese mix over top of the cooked cookie dough. Layer on the strawberry slices. Top with strawberry glaze. Refrigerate. Slice and serve.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Cover with water and add 1 cup salt.
Cook until tender.
Pour all the water off and then add dressing.
Bottle and seal while hot.

title: rich walnut fruit cake
directions: Sift the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and food coloring.
Add sifted dry ingredients with buttermilk; mix and fold in last.
Do not beat into batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 2 (9-inch) greased and floured pans or in Bundt pan.
Frost with white or red confectioners icing or drizzle glaze for that holiday touch.

title: debbie's marvelous meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix thoroughly 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce, beef, bread crumbs, onion and egg.
In 12 x 8-inch baking pan, firmly shape meat into 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: sin cake
directions: With fork, cut butter into cake mix until crumbly.
Add milk; mix.
Spread mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan (cake pan). Bake for 6 minutes in 350° oven.

title: simple saucy fish bake
directions: Thaw fillets just until they can be separated.
Heat oven to 475°.
Arrange fish in ungreased baking dish, 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inches, leaving space in center of dish.
Season fish with salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stir. Bring to a boil. Serve hot.

title: country crackling bread
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together and then stir in the cracklings. Beat the egg in the buttermilk and add.
Have melted fat in hot skillet and pour in batter.
Bake at 450° until light brown.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Put
brown
sugar, white sugar, butter and eggs in bowl and mix well, then add syrup, oatmeal, coconut and milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix together first three ingredients (1 1/2 cups sugar, eggs and pineapple).
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and brown sugar on top of cake batter.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°. Mix remaining 4 ingredients (Pet milk, oleo, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla) in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over hot baked cake.

title: stir-fried shrimp with vegetables
directions: Thinly slice carrots and mushrooms.
Thaw shrimp, if frozen. Shell and devein shrimp.
Halve shrimp lengthwise.
Blend chicken broth into cornstarch; stir in soy sauce and set aside.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with fruit cocktail to creamed mixture; beat well.
Pour into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, nuts and coconut.
Sprinkle on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done and tender.
Remove skin and bones.
Cut up chicken into pieces and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix soups and sour cream together until well blended and spread over chicken.
Sprinkle package of stuffing on top.
Pour broth and melted margarine evenly over stuffing.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until lightly brown on top.

title: olive stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix cream cheese, chopped olives, onion and seasonings in medium sized bowl.
Spoon stuffing into mushroom caps.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Garnish each mushroom with an olive slice, if desired.
Makes 2 dozen hors d'oeuvres.

title: macaroni slaw salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package; drain.
Combine macaroni, eggs, cabbage and olives.
In bowl, mix mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar, salt and salad seasonings.
Fold into macaroni mixture. Chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: diane's homemade fudge
directions: In a large pot, combine sugar and evaporated milk.
Cook until it comes to a rolling boil.
Do not boil for more than 8 minutes. Remove from heat and add chips, marshmallows, vanilla, butter and pecans.
Mix well and spread on an ungreased baking sheet (use a fairly large one).
Let cool completely and cut
into squares. Makes about 6 dozen small squares.

title: french onion soup
directions: You will need a heavy 4-quart pan.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a 2-quart microproof casserole, combine onion, celery, green pepper, margarine and garlic.
Cover; microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt, parsley, pepper, mushrooms and shrimp.
Cover; microwave on Medium for 5 minutes.
Stir.
Add cooked rice; microwave on Medium for 5 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes before serving.

title: picante con questo dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Over low heat, heat until sauce is smooth.
Serve with chips or vegetable dippers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: icebox cake
directions: Mix flour, margarine and walnuts; spread into bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan
and
bake
at 350° for 20 minutes, then cool. Mix cream cheese,
confectioners
sugar
and
one 9 ounce Cool Whip and spread	over crust.
Mix 2 packages chocolate instant pudding with 3
cups milk and pour over top.
Spread remaining Cool Whip; sprinkle walnuts.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook and debone (if necessary) chicken.
Pull apart into large chunks.
Set aside.
Saute onion and add chopped, peeled chiles, cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Add chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
In a 9x13-inch pan place a layer of tortilla chips, layer of chicken mix and a layer of cheeses.
Repeat layers until the pan is full.
Heat at 350 degrees until hot and bubbling.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding; stir in Cool Whip and rest of ingredients.
Chill.

title: pretty maple carrots
directions: Slice carrots into 1/8-inch thick rounds.
Steam, covered, over boiling water for 10 minutes.
Melt butter in a large saucepan and add maple syrup.
Stir.
Add the carrots, basil and salt.
Stir gently until carrots are well coated with the sauce and basil leaves.
Pour into an attractive bowl to serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, oil and carrots. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Combine bread cubes and celery in buttered 3-quart casserole. Arrange chicken over mixture and sprinkle with onion.
Combine eggs (slightly beaten), soup, milk and poultry seasoning.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over chicken.
Combine flour and cheese. Cut in the butter.
Sprinkle this over the rest, then top with slivered almonds, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes. (It's ready when a knife inserted in center comes out clean.)

title: waffles(makes 8 waffles)
directions: Coat cold waffle maker with no-stick vegetable spray. Heat waffle maker per manufacturers directions.

title: barley soup
directions: Cook barley by itself then add remaining ingredients. Simmer.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of large baking dish. Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning and 1/4 c. water to ground beef and cook 5 minutes.
Layer meat mixture over cream cheese.
Pour 1/2 sauce over meat.
Chop tomatoes and layer with olives next.
Pour on remaining taco sauce and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 325 until cheese melts, about 20 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: karen's mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Place in a microwave dish.
Lavishly coat with the salad dressing.
Cover and microwave at 100% power (full sized oven) for 5 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
Use sheet pan.
After removing from pan, poke holes in cake with wooden spoon handle.
Whip together the condensed milk and coconut milk.
Pour into holes in cake.
Cool for 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Chill evaporated milk in refrigerator overnight.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Mix in lemon juice, sugar and lemon rind.
Place in refrigerator until slightly thickened.
Whip chilled milk in a large bowl until thick.
Add gelatin mixture, whip together and mix well.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass dish with cookie crumbs and press firm.
Save a few crumbs to sprinkle on top of mixture.
Add mixture slowly in dish.
Spread evenly.
Chill in refrigerator 3 1/2 hours or overnight.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Mix oleo or butter
with sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add
vanilla and sour cream.
Mix dry ingredients and add to
creamy
mixture.
Stir
in
nuts, raisins and cherries.
Bake at 350° for
hour
and 5 minutes in lightly greased and floured tube pan or 2 bread pans.

title: bell ringer punch
directions: Combine juices well. Add Sprite before serving. Serve over ice in punch bowl.

title: trash
directions: In a dishpan combine cereals, pretzels and pecans.
In a saucepan melt butter and add all seasonings.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Bake in 325° oven, stirring regularly until pecans are done.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: snow cups
directions: Beat egg whites, vanilla, cream of tartar and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until very stiff peaks form.
Take 50 pieces of morsels for top.
Carefully fold remaining chocolate pieces into egg white mixture.
Cover baking sheet with brown paper bags (cut).
Drop mixture by teaspoon onto paper.
Top with chocolate bits.
Bake slowly at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Remove cookies from paper to cooling rack while slightly warm.

title: jiffy cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water until only 1 cup of water remains. Sift together next 6 ingredients.
Add melted butter to the water and raisins. Mix all together and add vanilla.
Bake on cookie sheet 15 minutes at 350°.

title: shipwreck
directions: Melt margarine in the bottom of a sheet cake pan or oven roaster (or Dutch oven if cooking outdoors).
Beat and add eggs and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Stir gently to loosen edges. Return to oven for 10 minutes (should be almost soft set).
Add all remaining ingredients and return to oven, covered for 10 to 15 minutes until eggs are set to your liking.
Serves 12.

title: make ahead breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet.
Cook until brown.
Drain. Spread cubed bread in a 12 x 12 buttered baking dish.
Top with sausage, onions,
green pepper and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings, beat well.
Pour over sausage, cheese, onions and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off top of peppers and clean.
Remove all seeds and membrane.
Parboil for about two minutes; drain.
Brown the ground beef; drain.
Cook the rice until tender in salt water and add to ground beef.
Add 1/2 cup salad dressing.
Mix well and stuff each pepper.

title: mamie's yams
directions: Boil the yams with the skins left on until tender.
Take them out of the water and cool.
Peel the yams and mash them.
Add orange juice, orange peel, vanilla, nutmeg, cinnamon and butter. Mix well.
Beat the egg lightly.
Mix the milk and fructose into the beaten egg and add this mixture to the yams.
Beat with a rotary beater until fluffy.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Turn off the oven and leave the yams in it for 1/2 hour longer.
This makes a nice cold side dish with a leftover turkey sandwich.

title: ornamental frosting
directions: Sift together confectioners sugar and cream of tartar.
Add egg whites and vanilla.
Beat with electric
beater until frosting holds its shape.
Tint with food coloring.
Cover with damp cloth when not in use.

title: dana's favorite milkshake
directions: Mash banana with fork and add to milk, ice cream and honey. Shake vigorously in a plastic container.
Be sure to check that the lid is on tight!
Pour into glasses.
Sprinkle a little wheat germ or cinnamon on top and enjoy with a friend!
Serves 2.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix well.
Put mixture into cookie press.
Press onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: picante dip
directions: Heat refried beans, then spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or any serving dish.
Add the remaining ingredients in layers, picante sauce, sour cream, tomatoes, onions, cheese and olives. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pig lickin cake
directions: Beat together and bake in 3 layers at 350° for 20 minutes. Let cool completely and ice with Icing For Pig Lickin Cake.

title: casserole-for-a-crowd
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion.
Cook until tender, but not brown. Add next 8 ingredients; mix well.
Stir in noodles.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a mixing bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, baking powder and nutmeg.
In another mixing bowl, combine sugar, shredded zucchini, cooking oil, egg and lemon peel.
Mix well. Add flour mixture.
Stir just until combined.
Stir in chopped walnuts.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, flour and onion together. Mix in corn, cheese and bread cubes.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: christmas day rice pudding
directions: Boil all ingredients together for 2 hours.
Add cinnamon and raisins after pudding cools.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion soup and bell pepper together.
Tear dried beef into small pieces and mix with cream cheese mixture. Roll in chopped nuts if desired.
Chill.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat well. Add mashed bananas, flour, soda, vanilla and nuts.
Grease and flour 1 large loaf pan.
Pour dough into pan.
Bake at 300° until brown (approximately 1 hour).

title: tuna tetrazzini
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Flake tuna with fork.
Mix soup with water.
Combine ingredients, except 2 tablespoons of cheese, in 3-cup casserole.
Toss lightly.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt white chocolate in microwave; let cool slightly.
Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add chocolate.
Then add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift dry ingredients and add to egg mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for angel food pan or 40 minutes for layered (three 9-inch round pans).
Cool before icing.

title: coconut snowballs
directions: Grease cookie sheets.
Preheat oven to 350°.
With electric mixer, beat butter until creamy. Gradually beat in sugar. Add vanilla.
On sheet of foil, stir together flour and salt. Add to butter mixture, blending well. Form dough into 1-inch balls.
If too soft, refrigerate dough for 2 hours. Roll into flaked coconut and place on prepared cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: carrot cake(serves 12)
directions: Beat until light.
Stir in 3 cups grated carrots.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Add sugar to eggs.
Sift flour into egg mixture.
Melt chocolate in margarine and add to mixture.
Mix well and add vanilla and walnuts.
Spread in greased square pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares when cooled.
Serves 6.

title: sue's salad
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Put sugar and 1/2 cup pineapple juice on stove.
Stir to dissolve sugar on low heat.
Add softened Knox gelatine.
Dissolve well.
Cool and add pineapple and cottage cheese.
Carefully fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into bowl and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Keep refrigerated.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine crushed flakes and spices.
Dip chicken breasts into buttermilk.
Cover with flakes and spice mixture.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Arrange chicken in dish.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken-vegetable spaghetti
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add chicken; cook, stirring constantly, until no longer pink.
Drain chicken and set aside, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings in skillet.

title: wet bottom shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and shortening together to make fine crumbs. Set 1/2 cup aside.
Add syrup and egg to remaining flour mixture, mixing well.
Stir in 3/4 cup of hot water; mix well.
Add soda to 1/4 cup hot water and promptly add to mixture; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle the 1/2 cup of crumbs on top.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 25 minutes longer or until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients
in
a covered jar and shake well. Refrigerate.
Shake well before using.
Makes 1 cup.

title: turkey sausage patties
directions: In a bowl, combine turkey, herbs and bread crumbs.
Stir well. Add chicken broth and stir again.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Form into 8 patties, about 3/4-inch thick.
Spray skillet with vegetable oil or use a nonstick skillet.
Cook patties in skillet over medium heat 7 to 8 minutes on each side or until done.
Serve hot.
Serves 8 with 1 patty per serving.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients and toss lightly with vegetables.
Chill overnight.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Layer chicken and a little broth. Layer sliced onion. Pour Ro-Tel; stir. Layer cheese and corn chips. Mix cream soups and pour over corn chips. Sprinkle corn chips on top. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to an hour (uncovered).

title: cough medicine
directions: Put the candy in the water and melt it.
Then strain the threads out and cook to about 1 quart.
Add lemon juice and glycerine.
Take 1 teaspoon every 3 hours or as needed until cough gets better.

title: classic meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion, Worcestershire sauce, egg and pepper.
In 12 x 8-inch baking dish, firmly shape into 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Spoon off fat, reserving 1 to 2 tablespoons drippings.
In 1-quart saucepan over medium heat, combine remaining soup, water and reserved drippings.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Serve with meat loaf.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chip beef cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well. Shape into ball and refrigerate.

title: scallops with walnut butter
directions: One hour before cooking, wash and drain scallops.
Place in a Zip-loc bag and add beer.
Refrigerate.

title: no peek beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 2-quart casserole dish and cover tightly.
(I use a Corning Ware dish with glass lid.)
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Do not peek.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: oven roasted barbecue brisket
directions: Trim brisket.
Mix all ingredients and cover all sides of brisket with paste (recipe to follow).
Place in foil lined pan, fat side up.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Cook brisket 1 hour per pound.
When there is only 1 hour left to cook, remove from oven and pour off juices.
Cover with barbecue sauce and onion slices.
Recover with foil and return to oven.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing across the grain.

title: aunt mary's doughnuts
directions: Roll and cut out; deep fry.

title: corn dressing
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese and pour into greased baking dish.
Spread cheese on top and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Good served with cranberry sauce.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add 1 medium onion with taco spice.
In large kettle, heat tomato sauce.
Add kidney beans and tomatoes; add browned meat.
Serve hot with grated cheese, sour cream and taco chips.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix all in bowl. Blend well and pour into crust. Bake until brown, 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into large bowl. Pour in Starter and butter.
Mix to make a firm dough.
Grease a 12-inch iron skillet with shortening.
Pinch off balls the size of walnuts.
Place in pan.
Set biscuits in warm place for 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake in a 400° oven for 24 to 30 minutes.

title: fudgy caramel apples
directions: Remove stem and blossom end of each apple.
Insert wooden skewers in stem end of apples.
In top of double boiler over hot water, heat butter and water until butter melts.
Stir in frosting mix (dry) until smooth.
Heat over boiling water 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; keep caramel mixture over hot water.
Dip apples, one at a time, in caramel mixture, coating apples evenly.
Immediately dip each caramel apple in chopped nuts.
Add a few drops hot water if caramel mixture becomes too thick.
When set, wrap apples in plastic wrap for storage.

title: spinach dip
directions: Let spinach thaw and drain.
Mix sour cream, soup mix and onions; set overnight in refrigerator.
Mix all ingredients in blender.
Hollow out pumpernickel bread and fill with dip.

title: five-layer dinner
directions: Arrange bacon in bottom of skillet.
Place beef patties over bacon; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place potatoes over beef; season with salt and pepper.
Layer carrots and onion over potatoes.
Cook on low until bacon starts to sizzle.
Pour in water.
Cook, covered, for 45 minutes or until done.

title: easy meatballs
directions: Mix together meat, rice, egg, onion and salt and pepper.
In a separate bowl, mix soup and milk.
Take 1/4 cup of this mixture and add to the meat mixture.
Form meat into meatballs (approximately 18).

title: rice pie
directions: Cook rice, using liquid from pineapple, with water.
Add remaining ingredients and beat together.
Pour into pie plates sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 1 hour or until knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: corn and kidney bean salad
directions: Combine beans, corn, onion and green pepper in large bowl. Toss well; set aside.
Bring vinegar, water, sugar and red pepper to a boil in a small Pyrex or enamel pan (do not use aluminum). Cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in celery seed. Pour over the bean mixture; toss gently.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 12 servings.

title: tamale soup
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Drain.
Add with rest of ingredients except tamales in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low heat for 6 to 7 hours. Add tamales.
Re-cover and cook 30 minutes longer. Accompany with hot cornbread.

title: macaroni
directions: Bring water to a boil and add 1 tablespoon of salt.
Stir, then add 2 cups macaroni.
Mix macaroni and other ingredients together and bake at 350°, stirring every 15 minutes, for about 45 minutes.

title: polynesian baked chicken
directions: Shake chicken parts in paper bag with flour and seasoned salt. Melt margarine and rub 2 tablespoons of it into 2 large baking dishes.
Place in chicken and brush remaining margarine over each piece.
Bake 50 minutes at 350° or until browned. Combine juices, sugar, soy sauce, salt and cornstarch in saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat when thickened and add fruit.
Pour mixture over chicken, coating each piece.
Bake 10 minutes longer. Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix cheese and margarine.
Add flour and mix well.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Shape into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten each ball with a fork and bake at 375° 10 to 12 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Spray large casserole dish with Pam. Mix all ingredients well and put in dish.

title: layer salad
directions: Use other combinations that you like.
The apple and onion are super together!
Serves a big crowd.
Break lettuce into 13 x 9-inch pan or dish.
Sprinkle with desired amount of onion and pepper.
Dice apple into salt water, then drain.
Layer onions and pepper and apple over lettuce.
Spread mayonnaise over layers with a spatula.
Sprinkle mayonnaise with 2 tablespoons sugar (use no salt).
Top with crisp bacon pieces and shredded cheese.
Cover and chill 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Keeps well for a day or two.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese slightly.
Mix with Marshmallow Creme until mixture is smooth.
Serve with any fresh fruit.
You may use a larger jar of Marshmallow Creme if you prefer more of the marshmallow taste.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cook beef until well done, drain on paper towels.
Set aside.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, cheese, onion and set aside.
Mix Bisquick and water until a soft dough is formed, pat in dish pressing well up sides of pan.
Layer beef, sliced tomatoes and green pepper over dough, spoon top with sour cream mixture, sprinkle with paprika and bake until edges of dough are light brown, about 35 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: fast goodies
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon into greased miniature muffin pans.
Bake at 450 for 10-12 minutes.
Yield: About 48.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Blend in oil, sugar and egg yolks and beat well.
Add hot water and then dry ingredients that have been sifted together. Stir in potatoes and nuts and beat.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake in 3 cake pans at 350° until done.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder in bowl.
Add oil, egg and milk.
Mix by hand.
Bake in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 20 minutes.

title: special cornbread
directions: In a medium size bowl mix all ingredients.
Bake in a 9-inch skillet at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies as directed.
Cool.
Make up instant pudding as directed.
Crumble candy bars.

title: apple bars
directions: Combine the 2 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar and baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter until crumbs are size of small peas.
Stir in egg yolks.
Divide mixture in half.
Press one-half over bottom of 15 x 10-inch baking sheet.
Combine apples, the remaining sugar and flour and cinnamon.
Arrange over bottom crust.
Crumble the remaining dough over apples, brush with egg whites over all.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Drizzle with thin powdered sugar icing. Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: greek lemon-egg soup
directions: Heat the rice and broth in a large saucepan to boiling. Reduce heat to simmering; cover and cook 15 minutes or until the rice is cooked. Add the chicken. Remove soup from the heat and cover. Whisk the eggs and lemon juice in a medium bowl until frothy. Remove about 1 cup hot broth from the soup and slowly add it to the eggs. Whisking continually, slowly stir warmed eggs into the soup. Ladle into bowls and serve immediately with a slice of lemon.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add fruit, nuts, marshmallows and condensed milk.
Chill until thick. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 11 x 13-inch dish to congeal.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling salted water for 5 minutes and drain.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrots.
Stir into drained, cool squash mixture.
Combine stuffing with butter in saucepan over low heat.
Spread half of stuffing mix in 4-quart baking dish.
Spoon squash over dressing mix and top with rest of dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: cheese danish
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Place 8 rolls on bottom of pan.
Flatten and stretch to form bottom crust.

title: quick and easy apple dumplings
directions: Peel and core apples and cut into 40 wedges.
Pat out biscuits and wrap two pieces of apple in each one.	Place in a 9 x 13 baking pan and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Mix Sprite, sugar and oleo and bring to a boil.
Pour over the dumplings and sprinkle lightly with cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 400° for about 12 to 15 minutes or until biscuits are a golden brown.

title: miracle rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set side.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking soda.
Cut in shortening. Blend until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in yeast and buttermilk.
Mix well.

title: lively lemon roll ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a small saucepan, melt margarine, stir in lemon juice, salt and pepper. In medium bowl, combine rice, broccoli, cheese and 1/4 c. lemon mixture, mix well. Divide broccoli mixture equally among fillets.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix and cook everything, except flour and soda, for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add flour and soda.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry dip for recital
directions: Wash and remove stems from fresh strawberries.
Arrange in a big tray the strawberries in a nice arrangement.
In the center, place a small dish with the strawberry dip.
Mix the marshmallow cream and cream cheese until creamy for the dip.
Dip each strawberry and enjoy it.

title: philly 3-step cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Pour into 1 prepared graham cracker crumb crust (9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Spread with 1 (21 ounce) can cherry pie filling. Makes 8 servings.

title: mystery cookies
directions: Melt
oleo.
Add
sugar
and vanilla.
Fold into flour, salt and baking powder,	add slightly beaten eggs.
Bake in 10 x 13-inch greased pan at 325° for 30 minutes or until it falls in middle. Cool, cut into squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: 5 hour beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in Dutch oven with a tight-fitting top. Bake 5 hours at 250°.

title: molded ambrosia
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add sugar and chill until partially set.
Add sour cream and vanilla; beat until fluffy. Fold in other ingredients and chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, onion, Cheez Whiz, soup, eggs and chilies together. Pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
